title: swedish sausage stew
directions: Lightly brown the sausage in a heavy, large skillet.
Remove and reserve.
Pour off the fat.
Melt the butter in the skillet. Saute the onion for 5 minutes.
Blend in the flour, then sir in the broth until mixture boils.
Add the sausage, potatoes, carrots, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil; cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: stewed corn and tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon till crisp.
Crumble and set aside.
Saut onion in bacon drippings until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 20 minutes over medium heat.
Add crumbled bacon before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and white sugar. Mix in egg, vanilla and water. Sift dry ingredients together (flour, salt and soda) and add to creamed mixture. Fold in oats, pecans and raisins. Drop by teaspoon and bake until golden brown.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Put mixture into a large canister.
Shake until well mixed. To serve, put 1/3 cup mix in mug.
Fill with hot water and enjoy!

title: chewy chocolate-chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars, margarine, eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy. Add flour, baking soda and oats; mix well. Add chocolate chips. Drop on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti rotel
directions: Boil and debone chicken and save broth.
Cook vermicelli in chicken broth.
Chop and saute onion and pepper in margarine; combine vegetables, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms and cheese with vermicelli.
Stir until cheese melts and add chicken which has been torn into small bits.
Stir well.
Add some broth to assure a moist casserole.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: garden casserole au gratin for four
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a saucepan, cook vegetables in a small amount of boiling water for 5 to 8 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Drain and transfer to a 1-quart oven to table casserole dish.
Season with garlic salt and pepper.
Distribute Cheddar cheese evenly over the vegetables; pour in milk.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs; mix lightly.
Pour in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: holy bible cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes in a large pan. It will keep indefinitely and the recipe is 100 years old.
All the ingredients are in the Bible.

title: anadama bread
directions: Place cornmeal, oil, molasses and salt in large mixing bowl. Stir to mix and pour the two cups of boiling water over all.
Let cool.
Add the yeast.
Stir.
Add 5 or 6 cups of bread flour. Knead lightly.
Place in greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Knead again and place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Let rise again until double.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, until bread pulls away from the sides of pan.
Remove from pan; rub butter or oleo on top and sides.
Cool on cake racks.

title: yummy banana bread
directions: Cream the oil and sugar in a large bowl. Add beaten eggs and bananas. Sift all dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture.
Beat well. Fold in chopped nuts, milk and vanilla. Bake in standard loaf pan (buttered and floured) at 350° for 1 hour. (Test with toothpick to be sure).
Hot from oven, cover with Karo (spooning on) and let set in pan until Karo dries to touch. Invert out of pan and wrap in foil.

title: impossible custard pie
directions: Mix first six ingredients in blender.
Pour into well-greased pie plate.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding mix and cold milk together until smooth.
Add Eagle Brand milk, sour cream, vanilla and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Beat until fluffy.
Alternate layers of pudding mix, vanilla wafers and bananas.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nutmeg; garnish with vanilla wafers.
Refrigerate.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste and 1 cup water.
Stir until blended.
Add oregano, bay leaves, garlic powder and onion.
Adjust to taste.
Simmer for at least 30 minutes for full flavor.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix ingredients for crust and pat into 13 x 9-inch pan; cover bottom and sides.
Refrigerate for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Have milk and eggs at room temperature. Sift dry ingredients together twice. Cream sugar and shortening real well; add eggs one at a time and beat until sugar is dissolved. Add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately, add lemon and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured tube pan baking at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan before taking out.

title: rice cooker black-eyed peas and sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use seasonings to taste.
Pour into rice cooker; stir.
Turn on rice cooker.
Done when "dings." Enjoy.

title: potato fritters
directions: In a bowl, combine and blend well the potatoes, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in the eggs and the 2 tablespoons vegetable oil, mixing thoroughly.
In a frying pan, heat 1/2-inch of oil until it is hot enough, when a small amount of mixture is dropped into it instantly it sizzles.
Drop heaping teaspoonful of the mixture into the hot oil.
Do not crowd.
Taste one of the fritters for seasonings.
Stir mixture each time before dropping into oil. When the bottoms of the fritters are crisply golden turn and brown the other side.
Drain on paper towel and serve immediately.

title: jiffy holiday pecan pie
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs and milk together, then add spices.
Heat oil in a skillet.
Dip each side of the bread into the egg mixture, one slice at a time. Fry until golden; flip and fry the other side until golden.

title: geri's cheese ball
directions: Soften all cheeses.
Mix with electric beaters with Worcestershire and garlic salt.
Add parsley flakes (2 tablespoons, more or less to taste).
Add 1/2 package of pecans. Spread remaining pecans and parsley on wax paper.
Roll cheese ball in mixture.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: sarma with cabbage
directions: Cook rice and mix together all of the ingredients.
Take one head of cabbage and peel off leaves.
Make a ball of the meat mixture and wrap the cabbage leaves around it.
Place cabbage in a pot.
Then add water until it just covers the cabbage.
Stew 2 medium sized tomatoes and add to the water.
Bring to low boil and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour with 1 cup water by putting into a closed jar and shaking.
Add to the pot and cook 30 minutes longer or until cabbage is tender.

title: noodle candy
directions: Melt tidbit morsels over low heat.
Mix in peanut butter and milk.
Stir in noodles.
Spoon in small portions and place on waxed paper.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, butter, egg yolks, flour, milk and coconut in saucepan. Cook over low heat until thick. Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue. Sprinkle top with a little coconut and brown in 350° oven.

title: sweet corn
directions: To keep your corn
nice
and
yellow,
add
2 teaspoons lemon juice and 1 teaspoon
sugar
and 1 teaspoon salt to each quart jar of corn.
Fill with water and cold pack 3 hours.
If pressure canner is used, your corn is apt to turn dark.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and cook broccoli according to package directions.
Add rest of ingredients and mix altogether.
Spread in a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken 1
directions: Cover and cook in 500° oven for 15 minutes.
Uncover and cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco dip(layered on a large dish)
directions: Mix the cream cheese and seasoning together and put on bottom of dish.
Layer the rest of the ingredients in order.
Surround with tortilla chips.

title: beer sausage
directions: Slice sausages 1/4-inch thick.
Combine ingredients in crock-pot; cook on low heat overnight until tender.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, remove dark parts.
Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Fry in skillet until golden brown.

title: green tomato and pepper relish
directions: Grind together first 4 ingredients and sprinkle with salt. Let set 3 hours; drain well.
Boil together vinegar, sugar, mustard and allspice.
Add the well drained vegetables and cook for 25 minutes.
Pack in sterile jars and seal.
Makes 6 to 7 pints, according to size of vegetables.

title: wedding chicken
directions: Mix liquid ingredients and add chicken.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Pour off butter and add mixture.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour melted butter on top of crackers and sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbles.
Great frozen.
Only add topping when ready to cook.
Thaw before cooking.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Firmly press into the bottom and up the sides of a 9 inch pie plate.
Chill.

title: peppy stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in halves lengthwise.
Remove seeds and wash. Combine beef, rice, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 can sauce.
Put mixture into peppers in a large baking dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers. Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Baste occasionally.

title: no bake yum yums
directions: Mix sugar, chocolate, milk and margarine on low heat to boiling.
Mix graham crackers, walnuts and marshmallows.
Pour cooled mixture over dry ingredients.
By the teaspoon, roll in coconut with buttered hands.
Place on waxed paper.
Makes about 80.

title: easy hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.
In a large skillet, saute the onion in the butter until tender but not browned. Add the hash browns, soup, sour cream, and milk. Stir well. Add the cheese, bell pepper, and pimiento.
Mix well and pour into a shallow casserole.
Sprinkle the cracker crumbs over the top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini beef skillet
directions: Saute beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until well browned. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.
I double or triple this and freeze for later use.

title: rosemary pork chops
directions: In a small bowl, mix oil, rosemary, garlic, salt and pepper. Brush mixture on both sides of pork chops and broil about 6 inches from heat for 5 to 7 minutes on each side or until cooked through.

title: thin pecan pies (3)
directions: Combine syrup and sugar and mix well.
Stir in eggs, melted butter and vanilla.
Pour 1 cup pecans in each pie shell and pour mix over it.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 thin pies.

title: baked pineapple chicken
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Combine reserved juice with garlic, cornstarch, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and rosemary.

title: pecan sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well the margarine, sugar, potatoes, egg, vanilla and milk.
Pour into glass pan.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix everything together, except popcorn and peanuts.
Bring mixture to boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour mixture over popcorn and peanuts.
Bake in 250° oven for one hour and stir every 15 minutes while baking.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet.
Press together.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing.
Spread on crescent rolls.
Sprinkle vegetables on top and press lightly.
Cut into small squares.

title: rosemary roasted chicken with potatoes and asparagus
directions: In a bowl toss chicken, garlic, onions and potatoes with oil and rosemary.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put into roasting pan.
Roast in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Lower oven to 350° and roast 20 minutes more.

title: fuzzy navel
directions: Combine ingredients in blender until creamy.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: carrot salad
directions: Peel, slice and cook carrots until tender; drain.
Add tomato soup.
Let set in refrigerator 12 hours.
Add celery, onion and bell pepper.
Bring to a boil the sugar, oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard.
Pour over vegetables. Cover and keep in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix together buttermilk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Stir in oranges, fruit cocktail, pineapple and pecans.
Chill until set.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Mix ingredients together, beating well. Place iron skillet on top of stove; pour in some bacon drippings and heat.
When hot, sprinkle cornmeal in pan.
Remove from heat and pour in cornbread batter and bake until done.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Spray a glass pie pan with nonstick coating.
Layer beginning with 1 cup Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese second layer, sprinkle with jalapenos and then remaining Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs; spoon over pie.
Sprinkle top with cayenne pepper or paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes, then cut in 2-inch sections for serving.

title: delightful crab salad
directions: Combine crabmeat, celery, olives, onion, mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Toss to mix.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco, sugar and eggs together at high speed for 1 minute.
Add 1 cup flour and beat 1 minute longer.
Add remaining flour and milk alternately.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° and then 10 minutes longer at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put sugar over cranberries and allow to stand for 20 minutes. Mix jello and hot water and allow to partially set.
Add nuts, orange and celery to berries.
Mix berries into jello and chill.

title: corinne's chicken casserole
directions: Put Ritz crackers in buttered casserole. Season green beans with Beau Monde.
Heat cheese in soup.
Layer with chicken, beans and sauce.
Cover with crumbs and almonds or with canned French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cover part of the time.

title: quick apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients except vinegar.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add vinegar after mixture has cooked 12 minutes.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Divide green beans into 12 to 15 "bundles."
Wrap 1 piece of bacon around each bundle.
Place bundles on cookie sheet or in a baking pan.

title: milky way icing
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla. Beat until spreading consistency.
One tablespoon cream may be added, if icing gets too thick.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer cooked and cut chicken in bottom of casserole.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Melt butter or margarine. Add crushed crackers on top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water in bowl; set aside a while, then add eggs and margarine to yeast mixture. (You may melt margarine and let cool some before adding to yeast mixture.)

title: a + punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in gallon jar and finish filling with water to make a full jar.
Slice orange and lemon slices in jar. Refrigerate.

title: rhubarb jam(miscellaneous)
directions: Boil rhubarb and sugar together for 12 minutes, stirring often.
Add the small can of crushed pineapple.
Remove from the heat and add the Jello.
Stir until the Jello is completely dissolved.
Pour into clean jam or jelly jars.
Refrigerate.
It will set in a couple of hours.

title: mother's irish bread
directions: Combine ingredients in order of listing.
Bake in greased and floured iron frying pan.
Brush top with milk when removed from oven to keep soft.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes, then 350° oven until baked.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cookies bake best when rack is placed in the middle of the oven so heat is equally distributed.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix ground beef, taco seasoning, water and picante sauce. Simmer about 5 minutes.
Spoon into flour tortillas.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese and roll up.
Place in baking dish and pour over top, chili and enchilada sauce that have been mixed and heated a little.
Spread shredded Cheddar cheese on top and bake in hot oven until cheese melts.

title: beef - ham roll-ups
directions: Spread slice of dried beef with mixture.
Roll up.
Cut in half.
Put a toothpick in if needed to hold together.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Shape dough into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls. Roll balls into cinnamon-sugar mixture until coated.
Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set, 6 to 8 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: burger pie(nanny hazel's)
directions: Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; put into crock or Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly and browned.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy brownies
directions: In medium size saucepan, melt butter and add sugar and eggs. Stir well.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake in buttered 8 x 10-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: one pot country chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with paprika, let stand for 5 minutes.
Saute onion and pepper in skillet.
Arrange potatoes in single layer over sauteed veggies. Salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken over potatoes and pour dissolved bouillon over.
Cook on low heat for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle peas around chicken.
Cover and simmer until chicken and peas are done.

title: never-fail pancake batter
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and milk.
Sift and add flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in shortening.

title: hazelnut shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Stir flour, sugar, salt and hazelnuts in medium-size bowl.
Cut butter into flour mixture with pastry blender.
Knead until mixture holds together.
Divide dough in half.
Place each half on an ungreased baking sheet.
Pat each out into a 9-inch circle; crimp edges.
Cut each circle into 12 equal wedges.
Do not separate.
Bake in a preheated oven (325°) for 30 to 35 minutes, or until golden brown.
Drizzle chocolate, if desired, over hot shortbread.
Cool 10 minutes.
Re-cut to separate wedges.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Prepare wild rice as directed on package.
Melt butter in saucepan, saute onion until tender.
Blend in flour; gradually add broth.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils; boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in rice, chicken and salt; simmer about 5 minutes.
Blend in half and half and sherry; heat to serving temperature.
Garnish with parsley or chives.
Serves 6.

title: pork stuffing
directions: Brown meat and onions until meat is done and onions are tender.
Boil potatoes, then rice or mash them.
Add to meat and onions.
Add salt, pepper and poultry seasoning to taste. Refrigerate until you are ready to use it.

title: oven steak with potatoes
directions: Cut steak in 6 to 8 pieces.
Add salt and pepper.
Dredge meat in flour; brown on both sides in oil in a 10-inch skillet.
Remove steak; saute onion.
Pour potatoes over onions; drain excess fat. Brown potatoes and onions for 5 minutes, turning frequently. Place meat on top of potatoes; add soup and water.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 35 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti cajun style
directions: Note:
Chicken breasts can be used instead.

title: marvelous meat loaf(makes 8 servings)
directions: In large bowl, thoroughly combine beef, bread crumbs, 1/2 cup steak sauce, eggs, pepper and onion.
Shape into 9 x 5-inch loaf. Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Brush with remaining steak sauce; bake 15 minutes more.

title: potatoes
directions: Put in 9 X 13 pan. Refrigerate over night. Bake in morning for 45 minutes.

title: dried beef ball
directions: Mix all together; form into a ball.
Sprinkle with paprika. Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate.

title: sleepy hollow tea room's chicken salad supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and grapes.
Garnish with pecans and grapes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot and bring to boil.
Lower heat and continue cooking until pasta shells are tender, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking to bottom of pot.
Remove bay leaf; fill blender with cooked soup once and puree; add back to soup.
Serve with Parmesan cheese on top.
Very filling.
Great for diets.
Can leave out pasta.
(If leaving out pasta, cook until carrots are tender.)

title: five bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mix lightly in large bowl. Finely chop celery, green pepper and onions and mix with beans. Boil vinegar, water, salt and sugar until sugar is dissolved. Then cool and pour over vegetables, mix lightly but well. Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.

title: almond tortellini salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Gently toss with dressing. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Chill.
Fold in almonds.

title: german apple cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in order; mix well.
Stir dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture.
Add apples. Batter will be quite stiff.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey bee wheat bread
directions: Mix yeast, warm water and honey. Set aside. Combine scalded milk, honey, oil and salt and let cool to lukewarm, then add to yeast mixture. Add flour to mixture. Mix and turn onto board. Knead until smooth. Place in greased bowl. Let rise until doubled. Punch down and divide into 2 greased loaf pans. Let rise again. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stan's chilli beans
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain.
Put in large cooker.
Put in undrained tomatoes, pinto, then put drained kidney beans, onion, green pepper, garlic, chili powder, salt and red and black pepper. Stir and put on high about 4 hours.

title: french market soup
directions: Soak beans overnight with 1 tablespoon salt.
Drain and put in large pot with ham or ham hock, chicken, bay leaves and 3
cups water;
simmer
covered
for
3 hours.
Add tomatoes, onions, garlic, celery and cayenne and simmer uncovered 1 1/2 hours.
If using
hock,
remove.
Chop lean ham and return to pot.
Remove chicken
bones;
return
chicken
to pot and add drained sausage. Add Worcestershire, Greek seasoning, Italian seasoning
and adjust
seasonings.
Watch while simmering and add water if needed.
Serve with salad and French bread.

title: square dance cake
directions: Mix together sugar, nuts and cinnamon; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients and beat 5 minutes.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan (do not use glass).
Pour 1/2 batter into pan. Sprinkle 1/2 of sugar mixture; add remaining batter and sprinkle remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then 30 to 40 minutes more at 325°.

title: nana's cutout cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add other ingredients. Chill. Roll out very thin. Cut in desired shapes. Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour in pie shell.
Freeze four hours.

title: four pepper pasta
directions: About 30 minutes before serving; in saucepot, prepare mostaccioli as label directs using 2 teaspoons salt in water; drain.
Return pasta to saucepot.
Meanwhile, cut peppers and onions into 1/2 inch wide strips.
In 12-inch skillet, over medium high heat, in hot olive oil, cook peppers, onion and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt until vegetables are tender and brown; about 15 minutes.
Stir in sugar, vinegar, basil and cracked black pepper. Heat through.
Toss pepper mixture with pasta.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour melted butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread crumbs over butter.
Then sprinkle nuts, chips and coconut.
Pour condensed milk over that.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: gramma's creamed green beans and mushrooms
directions: Cook green beans to desired tenderness in salt water.
Drain. In large skillet, saute mushrooms in butter until soft.
Add half and half and cornstarch, then seasonings to taste.
Stir constantly.
Bring to boil, turn down heat until thickened.
Add cooked, drained green beans to mixture and simmer on low heat until all ingredients are coated.
Taste and adjust seasonings. Serves 8 to 10.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in chocolate.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into 16 squares.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes about 45 minutes before assembling.
Combine potatoes in a large mixing bowl with butter, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover for a while at first.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated until ready to cook.

title: fried rice #1
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add meats and vegetables.
Fry until vegetables are cooked.
Add salt, soy sauce and oyster sauce; cook 1 minute.
Add eggs.
Stir in rice.
Cook until done.
Add green onion.

title: cookies
directions: Mix well, roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Canned icing can be used as topping.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil noodles.
Brown ground beef and then add onion, green pepper and oregano.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce. In casserole dish, mix noodles, sauce and cheeses.
Sprinkle cheese on top and microwave for 5 to 10 minutes or until melted.

title: sweet and sour meatballs(appetizer)
directions: In large bowl, combine beef, crumbs, egg and 2 tsp. bouillon; mix well.
Shape into 1 1/4 inch balls.
In large skillet, brown meatballs, and remove from pan.
Pour off fat.
In same skillet, combine preserves, lemon and remaining bouillon, over low heat, cook and stir, about 10 minutes.
Add meatballs and simmer, uncovered for 10 minutes.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: coconut pudding(portuguese)
directions: Mix all together.
Butter baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Let pudding cool before removing from pan.
You can use a nice glass pan and leave pudding in it.
Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine milk, eggs and zucchini.
Add to dry ingredients, mix until moist.
Drop by tablespoon and fry in skillet with oil.
Drain.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix ingredients, chill and serve.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix meat, 1 package Sloppy Joes mix, eggs and bread crumbs. Make into meatballs.
Cook over medium heat.
Add 3 cups of water, tomato paste and other Sloppy Joes mix.
Cook for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Boil pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes.
Immediately poke holes (with wooden spoon handle) into cake when removed from oven.
Pour hot pineapple mixture over cake.
Cool; prepare pudding and put over cake.
Place sliced bananas over pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese, milk, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts and freeze overnight.
Can drizzle chocolate syrup over top when serving.

title: baked orzo casserole
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine pasta, Jack cheese and chiles on dish.
Spread sour cream on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: marshmallow fruit salad
directions: Combine fruits, nuts and sour cream in a large bowl.
Fold in whipped topping and marshmallows.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cheese baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in 1 tablespoon melted butter, then in the Parmesan cheese.
Melt remaining butter in shallow pie plate. Bake in a hot oven (400°) about 50 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Spoon drippings over chicken once or twice during baking. Cover with foil the last 15 minutes to prevent overbrowning. Serves 2.

title: grandma estelle's mandel bread
directions: Into a mixing bowl, place shortening and sugar and beat until light and creamy.
Add the eggs and vanilla, beating to mix.
Mix together the flour and baking powder, then add to the shortening-egg mixture and beat slowly to mix.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Add sauces and mushrooms. Simmer.
Cook noodles.
Layer in crock-pot the hamburger mixture, noodles and cheeses until full.
Cook on low until cheese melts.

title: chicken scramble skillet
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasoning. Let thaw. Add Italian dressing to skillet. Add chicken and cook on low heat. Cook until dressing has evaporated, leaving just the oil. Steam the veggies with the butter in the microwave. Remove chicken and cut up. Add back to the skillet. Add remaining ingredients; simmer until hot.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off grease and add all the ingredients except the pork and beans.
Mix all the ingredients well, then add the pork and beans.
Place in a casserole bowl. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: larraine's chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix and blend all 5 ingredients with spoon or spatula.
Fold in 1 bar German sweet chocolate which has been grated and 6 ounce package Nestle chocolate chips.
Bake in Bundt pan (greased) at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Boil noodles.
Add hamburger to sauce.
Add Parmesan cheese and garlic.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ricotta cheese cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Then add cheese and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Shape cookies in a walnut size on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: upside-down pizza casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef, onions and pepper. Drain.
Stir in pizza sauce, pepperoni, Italian seasoning and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on floured surface.
Knead 20 times.
Pat dough on bottom and up sides with floured hands.
Brown sausage, onion, salt and garlic; drain.
Mix tomato sauce and Italian seasoning; spread evenly over dough.
Spoon sausage mixture over sauce.
Top with mushrooms, green pepper and cheese.
Bake until crust is golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Lightly grease three 9-inch diameter round cake pans and line bottoms with waxed paper. Using electric mixture, beat sugar and oil until creamed. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg into sugar and oil mixture. Stir in carrots, chopped pecans and currants. Pour batter into center prepared pans and bake about 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center. Cool in pans on racks. When semi-cool, turn cakes out onto racks and let cool completely.

title: bacardi pina colada pudding cake(stir up some excitement with this special exotic concoction.)
directions: Blend all ingredients
except
coconut	in
large mixer bowl. Beat 4 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Pour into 2 greased and
floured
9-inch
layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes	or
until cakes spring back when lightly pressed.
Do not underbake.
Cool
in
pan
15 minutes; remove and
cool
on racks.
Fill and frost;
sprinkle with coconut. Chill. Refrigerate leftover cake.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Place in greased rectangular baking dish.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: 5 bean dish
directions: Fry bacon; drain fat. Crumble. Drain 5 cans of beans and put in crock-pot.
Mix sugars and ketchup; add to crock-pot. Add bacon and chopped onions. Stir. Cook on slow 6 to 8 hours.

title: marinated cabbage
directions: Mix all together.
Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: dog-n-cheese-n-bun
directions: Cut a slit in each hot dog, put 1/2 slice of cheese in each. Roll up in crescent roll and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Oil muffin tins.
In a large bowl, cream together 1/2 cup of butter and 3/4 cup of sugar.
Add the egg, beating well.
In a separate bowl, combine 2 cups of flour, baking powder and salt. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Fold in the blueberries.
Fill the prepared muffin tins 2/3 full.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix shortening, flour, salt and then add buttermilk.
Makes 5 pies.
Keeps in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: cheese crabbies(a hot hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Halve English muffins.
Mix softened butter with crabmeat and cheese.
Spread on muffins to edges.
Broil on cookie sheet until brown and puffed.
Cut into wedged quarters to serve as hors d'oeuvre.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornbread mix.
Add last and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: ginger-spiced chicken
directions: Saute chicken
and garlic in oil until lightly browned, about 4
minutes.
Stir
in
mixed
vegetables.
Cook and stir until crisp
and tender, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine water, cornstarch and soy sauce in small bowl, stirring until smooth. Stir in
chicken mixture.
Add ginger and bouillon cube.
Cook and stir
over medium heat until mixture thickens and comes to boil. Cook 1 minute.
Spoon over rice.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream together; stir in beans.
Spread in casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Mix saltines and margarine together until all crackers are covered and no butter is left. Spread this mixture over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water and sugar. Add to this frozen juices.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: cream pie filling
directions: Blend together half the sugar, flour and salt.
Stir slowly into hot milk and cook until thick.
Add yolks, beaten with remainder of mixture and cook 1 minute longer.
Remove from fire and stir in the butter and vanilla.
When cool, you may add fruit or coconut.
Banana and strawberry are our favorites.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: potato bread with caraway seed
directions: Scrub potatoes and boil in skins until tender.
Drain them, then peel and mash.
Allow potatoes to cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of warm water, mix well with 3 tablespoons of flour in large bowl and let this starter rise for 30 minutes.
Add the remaining 2 cups of warm water, the salt, caraway seed, then the remainder of flour and mashed potatoes and mix well.
Turn out on a floured board and knead until the dough is elastic (12 to 15 minutes). Shape into ball.
Oil a bowl, put dough in it and coat dough with oil.
Place in warm, draft-free spot for 1 to 2 hours to rise until doubled in bulk.

title: cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place cheese, miracle whip, and onion in food processor and blend thoroughly. Spread over bread. Bake 10 minutes or until lightly toasted.

title: fruit torte
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, baking powder and eggs. Beat well.
Spoon batter into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Place fruit on top of batter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove and cool.

title: calabacitas
directions: Combine zucchini, green chilies, corn and liquid in saucepan. Bring to boil.
When zucchini is tender, drain liquid.
Add grated cheese.
Cover and let cheese melt.
Stir thoroughly.
Serve as a side dish to meat, tacos, use your imagination.
This recipe is from Santa Fe, New Mexico and it's delicious.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Blend flour and Crisco.
Stir in cheese. Mix mustard and soda into buttermilk.
Stir buttermilk into flour mixture.
Roll out biscuits. Place on greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Peel apples and cut into small chunks, about the size of a thimble.

Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Mix and set aside. Beat remaining ingredients together until smooth and pour half of the batter into a greased tube pan. Arrange 1/2 of the apple mixture over the batter. Pour in remaining batter and top with the rest of apple mixture. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done. Cake should be a golden brown in color. Remove and let cool a few minutes. Then remove from the pan and let cool on the rack.

title: salad
directions: Layer in bowl as listed.
Spread with layer of mayonnaise approximately 1/3-inch thick.
Sprinkle with approximately 1 1/2 tablespoons of sugar.
Cover with 1/2 to 1 c. grated cheese. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, oil, water and sugar in regular size bowl. Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; add to pumpkin mixture.
Either grease and flour loaf pans or tear off strips of waxed paper to line pans.
Use either 3 small ones or 2 large loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool 4 to 5 minutes and turn out on wire rack to cool.
This freezes well and can be baked in foil pans for gifts.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and leeks in chicken stock for about 15 minutes or until the potatoes start to disintegrate.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Work in the butter and serve with a sprinkling of grated cheese.

title: tangy lemon crunch
directions: Mix flour, sugar, rolled oats, baking soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Press half of this dry mixture in bottom of a well buttered square 9-inch cake pan.
Cover with Lucky Leaf lemon pie filling.
Spread remaining crumb mixture evenly over the top.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes.

title: oh-so-good brownies
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and water and bring just to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate bits and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate melts.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together; add nuts.
Spread in 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: In a casserole pan, alternate layers of chili, chips and cheese.
Makes 2 layers of each, ending with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until dish is bubbly hot.

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Heat oil in a heavy skillet.
Add onion and ground beef.
Stir with fork to break up the ground beef and brown.
Add chilies, soup and enchilada sauce.
Mix well and cook for 10 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Mix with crumbled Ritz crackers. Mix butter and crackers and line the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Save some cracker crumbs for the top of the cake.
Soften ice cream.
Beat in the milk and instant pudding; mix well.
Place mixture over crumbs.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle crumbs over the top.
Refrigerate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix everything together in a large bowl.
Put mixture in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with 2 cups of crushed corn flakes.
Melt another 1/4 cup of oleo and pour over the mixture. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ham salad
directions: Grind in meat grinder the bologna, onion and eggs.
Put in large bowl.
Add relish.
Make on stove in saucepan the Miracle Whip and mustard; thin it with milk, a little at a time, until you can pour it like a thin sauce.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Make it kind of sweet.
Pour over ground ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Serves a very large group of people.

title: chicken chard and rice soup(nice with a crusty loaf of bread)
directions: Wash the chard well; cut into 1/2-inch wide strips, both leaves and stalks.
In a 4 to 5-quart pot, melt the butter.
Add the onion; saute over medium heat until softened.
Add the chard; stir to coat with butter.
Cover the pot; heat for 4 to 5 minutes to wilt the chard.
Add 6 cups chicken broth; bring to a boil and add the rice.
Cover; cook over medium heat until the rice is done, about 20 minutes.
If the soup becomes too thick, add more broth. When rice is done, add the fresh Parmesan and parsley.
Taste for seasoning.
Serve hot with more cheese sprinkled on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mash bananas and add other ingredients.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: sugar-free lemon pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add yogurt and stir until smooth.
Refrigerate 15 to 30 minutes until slightly set.
Pour into baked pie shell and refrigerate until set.

title: scotch eggs(an appetizer)
directions: Dust eggs with flour.
Add a few drops of Worcestershire sauce, plus 1/2 teaspoon black pepper and 1/4 teaspoon sage to sausage meat; mix.
Divide into 6 equal portions.
Form each portion into a flat cake and work around egg, making sure there are no cracks.
Brush with beaten egg and toss in bread crumbs.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steak diagonally across grain into thin slices; cut into strips 2 inches long.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly, then fold in applesauce. Sift flour, spices and baking soda together.
Remove 1/4 cup of flour mixture and dredge nuts and raisins in it.
Fold remaining flour mixture into butter and sugar, then add vanilla and the nut and raisin mixture.
Mix well before pouring into prepared tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Put in attractive baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot with Doritos type chips.

title: hot fruit drink
directions: Let simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook until thick all ingredients except bananas and wafers. Line pan with wafers then bananas on bottom and sides.
Pour warm mixture over wafers and bananas.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Pour over pudding and brown in oven.

title: hot hamburger dip
directions: Saute meat in tiny bit of olive oil until brown.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and stir over low heat until cheese melts (double boiler works best).
Spoon into chafing dish and keep warm.
Serve with corn chips.

title: quick shrimp creole
directions: Chop onion, green pepper and celery.
Mince garlic clove and saute in oil for 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and boil for 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: s'mores
directions: Break chocolate bars into quarters.
Place chocolate on each of 8 graham crackers.
Toast marshmallow lightly and put on top of chocolate.
Sandwich with another graham cracker.
Then have s'more.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all of these by hand adding oranges and juice last.
Pour into 2 round cake pans or 1 oblong pan and bake 25 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in a large heavy saucepan and slowly bring to a rolling boil.
Let this boil for 8 minutes.
Remove the saucepan from the heat and add chocolate chips, marshmallows and butter.
Mix only until the chips and marshmallows are melted. Add vanilla and nuts. Blend.
Spread the mixture in a large ungreased pan or platter.
Let cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix until well blended.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: apple leather no. 2
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar and nutmeg.
Spread 1/2-inch thick in shallow pan.
Bake at 250° approximately 3 hours.
Remove when nearly dry and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: osgood pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Beat the egg yolks and fold in the rest of the ingredients, except the egg whites. Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into the mixture. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake at 400° for about 35 minutes.

title: hot chili french bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut loaf diagonally into 1-inch slices. Mix ingredients.
Spread on slices. Reassemble loaf and wrap up tightly in aluminum foil. Heat 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 24 slices.

title: john mozetti
directions: Brown ground beef in 1 tablespoon oil. Add onions and peppers. Cook until done. Drain off part of grease. Add 1/2 of both cheeses and all other ingredients. Put in casserole dish and top with remaining cheese. Bake about 45 minutes at 375°. Serves about 6.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan; bring to boil. Remove from heat; cover and stand 5 minutes.
Cool.
Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine next 3 ingredients; add to butter mixture alternately with milk mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in lemon rind.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely before pouring glaze over bread.

title: greek pot roast
directions: In large pot, brown meat in oil and butter.
Add onion and garlic, brown a bit.
Add rest of vegetables, spices and tomato paste.
Cook several minutes.
Add the 6 cups hot water.
Bring to a boil.
Add wine.
Reduce heat, simmer for 2 to 3 hours, turning meat after 1 hour.

title: grandma's macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in milk.
Stir until begins to thicken.
Add salt and pepper.

title: fruit and cheese appetizer
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and mayonnaise, mixing until well blended.
Add cheese and apple; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with apple wedges and rye bread.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: rolls
directions: Soak yeast cake in lukewarm milk for 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients, stirring mixture into soft dough.
(Add more milk, if needed.)
Let rise until mixture has doubled in bulk (about 2 hours).
Knead or stir well; shape into rolls.
Place in well-greased pan.
Let rise until rolls have doubled in bulk (about 1 hour).
Bake in moderate oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 24 rolls.

title: decorator icing
directions: Mix
sugar
and
water	until
smooth.	Add
Crisco and flavorings; blend about 30 seconds.
If too thin, add powdered sugar and
stir.
If too thick, add 1 teaspoon water and stir. It takes 2 recipes to ice and decorate a cake.

title: potato supreme
directions: Cook potatoes and let cool completely.
Potatoes can be cooked peeled or with peel on.
Coarsely grate potatoes and mix well with other ingredients.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven about 35 minutes.
Save some cheese to sprinkle on top.
This is a great dish for a crowd.
Can be prepared ahead of time.

title: chocolate walnut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, over low heat, melt margarine.
Add cocoa; stir until smooth.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, water and eggs.
Beat well.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla, flavoring and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set.
Cool slightly. Serve warm or chilled.

title: french fried cheese
directions: Cut cheeses into 1/2 inch cubes. Dip into egg, then crumbs. Repeat for second layer.
(A thick coating prevents the cheeses from leaking through.)
Pour oil into fondue cooker to no more than 1/2 full.
Heat on range to 375°.
Add 1 teaspoon salt. Transfer to fondue burner.
Spear cheeses with fondue fork and fry in hot oil for 1/2 minute.

title: dottie atkinson's french mints
directions: Sift
sugar.
Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add water, flavoring
and
food color and mix well by hand.
Roll into marble
size balls and dip in fine sugar.
Press sugared ball down in mold.
Remove any excess mixture to make it even with
the mold and unmold by putting a finger on all 4 corners of
the
mold with
your
thumb
on
the back of the mold and turning out on wax paper.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put mixer and beaters in freezer a couple of hours before starting.
(Oven must be on before gathering ingredients.)

title: chocolate kraut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla, add dry ingredients.
Add water, stir in kraut.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Prepare lettuce and then in a separate bowl, add together the lemon juice, salad oil, 1/2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce, ground pepper, salt, mashed garlic and dry mustard.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or so to cool.
In a salad bowl, mix lettuce with dressing mixture and coat all pieces.
Add Parmesan cheese and mix, then the croutons and mix well.
Serve and enjoy.

title: sweet and sour asparagus
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Place asparagus (from 2 large cans) in a flat dish and pour hot liquid over.
Store covered in refrigerator for 24 hours.
To serve, pour off liquid and sprinkle with grated cooked egg whites.

title: applesauce raisin chews
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add applesauce, egg and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually add combined flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 13 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter pizza
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar, oleo, peanut butter, vanilla and egg.
Blend well.
Mix in flour.
Press dough evenly over bottom of 12 x 14-inch pizza pan, forming rim along edges.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and chocolate chips. Continue to bake for 5 to 8 minutes or until marshmallows are puffy and lightly browned.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Mix salt, onion, celery, green pepper and butter.
Gradually stir in chicken broth and soup.
Cook until thickened.
Cook rice according to package directions including herbs and spices.
Mix sauce, rice and chicken.
Pour in large casserole.
Top with almonds.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.

title: burda's new potatoes
directions: Clean potatoes; peel and leave strip around the center.
In large pan, on stove top, saute butter and seasoning.
Add potatoes (cut in half if too large).
Cook for about 5 minutes; lightly brown.
Mix well.

title: prickly pear jelly
directions: Mix juice, sugar and lemon juice; bring to a boil.
Add pectin and boil for 5 minutes.
The longer the mixture boils, the thicker the jelly will be.
Remove the cooked mixture, skim off the foam, pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 6 (8 ounce) jars. Very good!

title: jiffy barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion in hot oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Drain grease off of ground beef mixture.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Let simmer 30 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer ground beef mixture, sour cream and noodles.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: vinegar dressing
directions: Uses:
Salad dressing, coleslaw dressing, chicken marinade.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars; mix to blend.
Add margarine and oil; beat well.
Add eggs, mix well.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and soda.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Form into small balls; dip cookie top into small amount of granulated sugar. Place on cookie sheet and flatten with bottom of a glass.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: chili mac
directions: In large heavy skillet or heavy pan, brown beef and cook onion with chili until tender; pour off fat.
Stir
to separate meat. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Makes 6 1/2 cups.

title: real boston baked beans
directions: Pick over beans and rinse.
Place in a large bowl; add water to cover; let stand overnight and drain.
Combine beans and onion in a large saucepan, add water to cover, heat to boiling and cover. Simmer 45 minutes or until skins of beans burst when you blow on several in a spoon.
Drain liquid into a small bowl.
Measure 1 cup of the bean liquid and combine with molasses, mustard, brown sugar and salt in a bowl.
Layer half of the salt pork and all of the beans into an 8-cup bean pot or baking dish.
Pour molasses mixture over top, add just enough more saved liquid to cover beans.
Top with remaining salt pork, pressing down into liquid; cover.
Bake in a slow oven (300°) 4 hours or use a crock-pot at medium setting. Uncover and bake 1 hour longer, or until beans are deep brown, tender and as dry as you like them.
After 2 hours of baking, check beans and if they seem dry, add more saved bean liquid to keep them moist.
This is a treat served with brown bread and butter.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling and pineapple in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour dry cake mix evenly over pie filling. Sprinkle nuts and margarine over top of dry cake mix. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: drizzle topped brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
In medium mixing bowl, combine baking mix, sugar and cocoa; mix with spoon or fork until thoroughly blended.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate chips. Spread into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely. Prepare Quick Vanilla Glaze.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle bread and cheese on top. Cook in medium oven for 30 minutes.

title: chili pie
directions: Butter dish and place green chilis on the bottom of the dish. Spread cheese on top of chilis.
tags: of Cracker Barrel sharp cheddar cheese

title: carrots lyonnaise
directions: Cook carrots in bouillon, covered, for 10 minutes.
In saucepan, melt oleo.
Add onion and cook, covered, slowly for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix in flour, salt, pepper and water and bring to a boil.
Add carrots and stock; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add pinch of sugar.
Serves 6.

title: spanish rice
directions: Partially fry bacon in pressure pan.
Add green pepper and onion; cook until onion is golden and bacon is crisp.
Add rice, tomatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Cook at 10 pounds pressure for 10 minutes.
Allow the pressure to go down normally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grits
directions: Mix water and grits.
Put in microwave (cook for 3 hours) then add butter or cheese.

title: good nuts!!(for pecans, walnuts or cashews)
directions: Soak nuts in water, sugar and honey mixture overnight.
Cook nut mixture on stove on high, stirring constantly.
Stir until fluid is gone.
Dump on waxed paper, stirring as they cool (they will stick)/dry (10 to 15 minutes).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda, salt, eggs, oil and water together. Add pumpkin, spices and other ingredients.
Pour into loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chow chow
directions: Mix.
Boil at a hard boil for 30 minutes.
Put in jar and seal.

title: simply delicious haystacks
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler over hot water, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Refrigerate until set.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 heart shaped or 9-inch round cake pans. Divide strawberries and juice in half.
Refrigerate half.
Pour remaining half in blender or food processor.
Measure puree and add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and gelatin.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Combine peanut butter, 2 tablespoons butter and confectioners sugar.
Stir in nuts.
Mix until smooth.
Shape into balls.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and chocolate pieces over low heat or hot water. Dip balls into chocolate.
Put on wax paper on cookie sheet and refrigerate.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and margarine.
Add syrup and mix.
Add flour, salt, soda and spices.
Mix well.
Add hot tap water.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy chili enchiladas
directions: Mix together chili, cheese and onions.
Blend well.
Separate a portion of filling to spread over top of enchiladas.
Spoon filling in each flour tortilla and roll.
Place in pan and spread remaining filling over top of enchiladas.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut tomatoes, onions, cabbage and corn in pieces.
Put in pot. Cook until cabbage is tender.
In another pot, pour vinegar. Add sugar to taste. Temper down with water.
Put vegetables in jars. Add 1 teaspoon salt to each jar.
Add pickle spice.
Pour hot vinegar. Seal jars and let set until cool. Store away.

title: strawberry pretzel
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; press in large pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries, partially thawed and mashed a little.
Refrigerate until almost set.

title: sweet lime pickles
directions: Dissolve lime thoroughly before adding the cucumbers; it won't all dissolve.
Let stand 24 hours.
Stir occasionally with hand or wooden spoon gently.
Take cucumbers out of lime water; rinse 3 or 4 times.
Let stand in cold water for 3 hours.
Drain in colander; put the solution over cucumbers.
Let set all day or overnight.

title: easy strawberry cobbler
directions: Place strawberries in baking dish.
Beat other ingredients together for 2 minutes.
Gradually pour beaten mixture over berries in swirls.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until top is golden brown.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, green pepper and onion in oiled casserole.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Mix soup with milk.
Pour over the potatoes.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are easily pierced with fork.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot and cook over medium heat until tender, then add mixture of 4 tablespoons flour and 3 cups of milk (shaken or mixed together) and 1 pound Velveeta cheese, cut into cubes.
Continue to simmer over low heat until the cheese is melted and add salt and pepper to taste.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks. Add milk and shortening.
Turn into dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites and add to batter. Dip batter onto hot waffle iron.

title: rice krispys
directions: Bring liquids and peanut butter to boil, add krispies and stir, remove from heat and drop on wax paper.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Heat soup, broth, and cheese till cheese is melted.

title: cocoa syrup
directions: Combine in saucepan the sugar, cocoa, salt and cold water to make a paste.
Blend in hot water.
Simmer 4 to 6 minutes, stirring until thick and smooth.
Cool and stir in vanilla extract.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and sugar together, then add pretzels.
Reserve 2 tablespoons mixture to topping.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes, cool.

title: granny's pie crust for chocolate fried pies
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls about the size of walnuts.
Chill.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon, onion, raisins and red pepper.

title: brandy peaches
directions: Boil these together.
Add peaches and boil until a straw can easily penetrate to the stone.
Take out the peaches and put into jars.
Mix equal parts of syrup and brandy and pour this over peaches, filling the jars and covering with syrup.
Seal.

title: strawberry angel cake dessert
directions: You will need a large mixing bowl with cover.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in glass bowl.
Cook 7 to 9 minutes on High.
Quickly stir in margarine and vanilla.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Take out and add soda.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Combine butter, pepper and garlic; spread into rectangle on a piece of foil; freeze until firm.
Take that butter and cut into 6 equal pieces.
Place one piece of butter on each chicken breast; fold in end and roll to encase the butter completely.
Secure with skewers or toothpicks.
Beat egg with water.
Coat chicken with seasoned flour; dip in egg mixture, then coat with bread crumbs. Place in shallow dish; chill 30 minutes.
Deep-fry chicken breasts in hot oil about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Keep warm in oven at 200° while remaining chicken is cooking.
Serve immediately.

title: microwave nutty chocolate bars
directions: Place butter in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Microwave at High for 45 seconds to 1 1/4 minutes or until butter melts.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Press mixture evenly in bottom of dish. Pour condensed milk evenly over crust.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and coconut.
Top with half the nuts.
Lightly press down. Place on upside down saucer in microwave.
Microwave at Power level 7 for 8 to 9 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Rotate every 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Cool.
Cut into 24 bars.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 to 1 cup of grated cheese and leave in oven just long enough to melt, but don't brown the cheese.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix together; shape into balls.
Lay in greased baking dish. Pour Ragu sauce over all or 1 cup mushroom soup and 1 cup tomato paste.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium size bowl, except cherries. Fold them in last, carefully, so not to crush them.
Chill for at least 30 minutes, then serve.

title: kielbasa and cabbage
directions: In large frying pan (electric if you have one) add everything except cabbage.
Cover and cook on medium heat until cabbage is half done, stirring often.	Slice kielbasa into 1/2-inch lengths and add to cabbage.
Cover and stir often until cabbage is done. Will come to golden brown.

title: spicy cherry punch
directions: Microwave (High) 2 cups water in uncovered 1-quart glass bowl 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until boiling.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Set aside.
Wrap cinnamon sticks and cloves in a piece of cheesecloth.
Tie securely.
Add 2 cups water in 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave (High) uncovered 3 to 4 minutes or until boiling. Add tea bags and allow to set, about 5 minutes.
Remove spice packet and tea bags.
Stir in sugar, lemon juice and gelatin mixture.
Refrigerate to chilled.
To serve, pour gelatin mixture in punch bowl.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Add Sprite.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef in pot and drain off grease.
Add chili sauce, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes stirring often.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Serves 6.

title: layered overnight salad
directions: Shred lettuce heads. Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add by layers the celery, onion, water chestnuts and peas.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over top. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Mix together sugar, salt and garlic powder.
Sprinkle over top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 10 hours, up to 24 hours.
Before serving, garnish with bacon, chopped eggs and tomatoes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt margarine, oil and marshmallows.
Pour over popcorn. Press into a greased Bundt or pound cake pan while warm.
Decorate the top with the few gumdrops.
When cake is cool, it will come out easily.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Assemble all ingredients and utensils.
In a large bowl, mix all dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, mix liquid ingredients.
Then stir together just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin tins which have been sprayed with a low calorie nonstick coating spray.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Calories 100, sodium 103 mg., carbohydrate 17 grams, fat 2 grams.

title: shake and bake for dieters
directions: Mix.
Coat chicken, then bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: southwestern macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain; rinse with hot water.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in same saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in flour, onion powder, salt, oregano and cayenne; blend well.
Cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook until mixture thickens and boils, stirring constantly.
Add vegetables and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 10 minutes and drain.
Mix all ingredients. Bake in slightly greased casserole dish at 400° for 30 minutes. Put 1 cup crushed crackers on top of the casserole for the last 10 minutes of baking or until golden brown.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix as for any cookie (I generally mix well after each ingredient). Roll into balls about the size of a walnut and dip in sugar. Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 375°. Bake about 3 minutes longer if you want crisp cookies.

title: salmon patties
directions: Flake salmon.
Add salt, pepper, lemon juice, cracker crumbs, eggs, milk and parsley.
Shape into patties.
Melt shortening and fry patties at 350° in a preheated fry pan until golden brown on both sides.
Garnish with lemon slices and parsley, if desired.

title: ambrosia waldorf salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
In a large bowl; combine apples, marshmallows, grapes, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in the cranberries and mix well.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Cover and chill.
May sprinkle with coconut before serving.

title: margies cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and make small balls, make a well with clothes pin or thumb; fill with jelly. Bake at 350° till done, about 12 to 15 minutes. Can shake powdered sugar on them.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix oil, water, vinegar and sugar.
Heat.
Let stand until cool.
Drain kraut; add pimento, celery, onion and green pepper. Mix all together.

title: easy quiche
directions: Cut bacon in 1/2-inch pieces and fry until very crisp.
Drain off fat.
Put cooled bacon pieces in pie shell.
Cover with shredded Swiss and chopped onion.
Heat cream and add to well-beaten eggs.
Add seasonings (very small amount of nutmeg). Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350°
oven for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon streusel bundt
directions: Combine the sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Place frozen cinnamon rolls in a bundt pan sprayed with non-stick cooking spray.
Sprinkle mixture over rolls.
Cover with plastic wrap, let rise until double in size (about 4-5 hours) at room temperature. Bake at 350 for 25-30 minutes.
Invert immediately on serving platter.
Microwave cream cheese frosting packet for 10 seconds. Snip off corner and drizzle on bundt.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into dish. Refrigerate until firm. Cover with thin layer sour cream.
Make up another mixture, same as previous, and pour over the layer of sour cream.
Put back in refrigerator until firm.

title: cheese strata
directions: Cut 12 circles from bread, set aside.
Fit scraps of bread (top crust removed) in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cheese over bread, add layer of broccoli, then ham.
Arrange circles on top. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 minutes. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top 5 minutes before end of baking time.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting into 12 squares. Parsley on top!
Serves 12.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; add ingredients.
Hand mix.
Pour into 8-inch pie pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers of choice.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg and one tablespoon water.
Roll chicken in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Brown in skillet with the small amount of shortening.
Stir in soup, one-quarter cup water, onion and seasonings.
Cover and cook on low heat about 30 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle with cheese; heat until cheese melts.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Add additional oregano if desired.

title: bean and cheese tacos
directions: Add Ro-Tel and oil to beans and simmer for 20 minutes.
Bean mixture can be served as is or whipped with a hand mixer.
Warm tortillas and fill with beans.
Top with grated cheese.
Ground beef or turkey can be added, if desired.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Layer first three ingredients in a pan.
Mix soup with enough milk to make 2 cups.
Add eggs to the mixture and pour over the chicken.
Bake at 375° until it bubbles.

title: fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line pan with foil.
Grease a rack and place in pan.
Mix crumbs and seasonings on waxed paper.
Coat chicken with yogurt using fingers.
Press crumbs on chicken to coat.
Place on rack spacing in between.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until coating is brown and juices run clear when pierced.

title: quick company salad
directions: Take fruit cocktail; add vanilla pudding, Cool Whip and sliced bananas.
Mix altogether.
Can be served immediately.

title: edna's rhinelander green beans
directions: Cut bacon in very small pieces and brown.
Add onion after bacon has browned.
Allow to cool.
Mix vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and cabbage.
Add this to bacon and onion.
Drain beans; add to cabbage/bacon mixture and simmer for several hours.
Drain off excess liquid before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Bring the water to a boil in a medium saucepan over medium heat.
Dissolve the bouillon cube in the boiling water.
Add the broccoli and cook for 5 to 6 minutes, until it is bright green and fork-tender.

title: jan's strawberry sour cream dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter and press firmly into bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: italian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken parts in flat roasting pan.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, salt, pepper, oregano and parsley.
Put a small pat of butter on each piece of chicken. Sprinkle paprika over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Baste now and then.
Mix together soup, wine and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 20 minutes longer, basting often with sauce.

title: bill's "warm your belly chili"
directions: Brown beef; add onion soup mix, chili powder, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Add tomato sauce and chili beans.
Cook over medium heat until desired consistency or until the aroma gets to you and you just have to taste some.

title: herbed parmesan chicken
directions: Cut chicken breast into pieces 1 1/2 to 2 inches wide.
Combine next 6 ingredients in a paper bag.
Coat chicken with mixture a few pieces at a time by shaking bag.
Place chicken in a baking dish and press any remaining seasoning into chicken.
Sprinkle chicken with oil and melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour wine over chicken and cover with foil.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove foil.
Raise heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes.

title: martha's taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Make your own salad the way you like.
Add taco seasoning to ground beef and add to salad.	Pour Catalina dressing to taste.
Enjoy!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and oil until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
Drop by heaping teaspoon on ungreased sheet.
Press down with sugared glass.

title: sausage, ham and egg souffle("bethany's easter breakfast")
directions: *You can use anything you like, hamburger, sausage, ham, Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella or American.

title: mother royer's english christmas pudding
directions: Mix sugar and baking powder with flour and sift.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs and remaining ingredients.
Have a 6-quart kettle 1/2 full of boiling water.
Put a small saucer in bottom of kettle.
After dough is wrapped in a 24-inch square of white cloth, tie a string 2 inches from top and put in boiling water for 2 hours over medium heat. Take from water and place on a large platter.
Slip out of cloth as it will glaze itself.
Can be served now or later with white sauce.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and lay next to the handle of wooden spoon. Slice 1/4-inch through potatoes, but not quite all the way.
(The spoon helps to prevent this.)
Put in baking dish and fan slices slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with oleo.
Add herbs. Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cheeses on top.
Return to oven 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: apple spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or shaker until white and foamy.
Pour dressing over salad just before serving.

title: applesauce cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg, well beaten.
Sift flour, spices, salt and soda three times together and add nuts and raisins, then add to the creamed mixture, alternating with applesauce.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: glazed pearl onions
directions: Bring pot of salted water to boil.
Add onions; cook 3 minutes to loosen skins.
Drain and cool.
Cut root ends from onions. Squeeze onions at stem end (onions will slip out of skins). Combine pearl onions, sherry, raisins, honey, water, butter and thyme in skillet.
Boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to very low; cover and simmer until liquid evaporates and onions caramelize.

title: cherry-coke gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cherries, sugar, pineapple (not drained) and pecan pieces to gelatin mixture.
Pour Coke down side of bowl, mixing carefully.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate and let congeal.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix Rice Krispies, chopped pecans and coconut.
Bake slow at 325° in 9 x 13-inch pan or dish for 30 minutes, stirring often. Mix in brown sugar and melted margarine; mix well.
Take half of mixture and pat firmly in bottom of pan or dish (9 x 13-inches). Slice ice cream and cover crumb mixture.
Cover with remaining half of crumb mixture.
Cover with foil or lid and freeze.

title: fried rice
directions: Melt butter in frying pan, add onions and any optional veggies.
Stir and cook until tender.
Push cooked veggies to side of pan- scramble eggs.
Put cold cooked rice over top of eggs and veggies. Mix together, frying until warm throughout.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Can add cubes of cooked meat!

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Melt Cheez Whiz in microwave. Saute celery and onions in margarine until tender.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Soak yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald milk and let it cool. Combine dry ingredients; add milk, water and yeast.
Work in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Let rise.
Roll out, cut and let rise.
Fry, top side down (first).

title: rice pudding
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Combine ingredients and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake slowly at 350° for 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.
May add raisins after removing from oven.

title: no knead crescent rolls
directions: Add sugar, oil, salt and cold water to scalded milk.
Mix well. Add eggs and yeast.
Gradually add flour, mixing well.
No kneading is necessary.
Cover bowl with waxed paper and towel.
Set in warm place and let rise until double.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll each part into 1/2-inch thick circles.
Cut each circle into 12 sections and roll up crescent shape.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise again.
Bake for 14 minutes at 350°.
Butter tops while still warm.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Beat eggs slightly Add milk and bread crumbs; let stand.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter.
Remove and add to crumb mix.
Add seasonings and meat; mixture will be soft.
Chill 1 hour to blend flavors.
Shape mixture into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls and brown slowly in remaining butter, turning easily.
Add more butter if necessary. Arrange in large baking dish.
Add flour to pan drippings and blend.
Cook until browned.
Add beef broth and simmer until thickened and smooth.
Add cream.
Sauce will be thin.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 325° in oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Bake in muffin pan 20 to 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange in layers in a 9 x 13-inch covered container.
Cover vegetables with mayonnaise and sugar.
Seal airtight and refrigerate for 6 hours.
Just before serving, sprinkle crumbled bacon pieces on top.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients into punch bowl.
Stir.
Do not add water to frozen cans.

title: doughnut holes
directions: In mixing bowl, combine eggs, milk, oil and vanilla; beat well with spoon.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt and add to milk mixture.
Blend together lightly with a spoon.
Do not beat.
Heat oil to 375°.
Dip spoon into hot oil until spoon is hot.
Quickly dip up 1 tablespoon of batter.
Dip in oil to drop off batter.
Cook about 4 minutes.
Drain and put powdered sugar on them when cool.
Enjoy!

title: salsa
directions: Cook for about 1/2 hour.
Thicken with cornstarch as you would gravy or strain in colander.

title: curried fruit bake
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and curry powder.
Drain and dry fruit. Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Add butter mixture and sprinkle almonds on top. Bake with oven meal for last 30 minutes.

title: sirloin tip roast
directions: Cut up vegetables.
Cook all together on low in crock-pot or at 350° in oven.

title: iced cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald milk and pour over margarine, sugar and salt.
Set aside to cool to lukewarm.
Add flour and beat.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water; add to first mixture.
Add eggs; mix well.
Soak raisins in hot water; drain good.
Add raisins to bread mixture. Add more flour to make moderately soft dough.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Dice onion and peppers.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, green onions and peppers in bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Spread a layer over the tortillas and roll up.
Continue until gone.
Put in pan; cover with foil and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Cut each roll into bite size pieces before serving.
May serve picante sauce for a dip.

title: butterfly toast
directions: Butter warm toast; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Cut toast into 4 pieces (corner to corner).
Move pieces apart just a little to make your butterfly.

title: walnut bread
directions: Beat egg; stir in milk, sugar and Bisquick.
Add walnuts. Bake in ungreased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
For variety, add 1/4 cup orange marmalade.

title: festive jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions on package.
Refrigerate until it has thickened.
Put marshmallows and a little heavy cream in top of a double boiler and melt.
Beat remaining heavy cream and cream cheese.
Add melted marshmallows and mix.
