Stir in drained pineapple and chopped nuts.
Add mixture to thicken Jell-O.
Pour into a mold.

title: asparagus casserole au gratin
directions: Drain asparagus, reserving liquid.
Cut asparagus into 1-inch pieces.
Combine asparagus and reserved liquid with next 5 ingredients in 2-quart casserole; mix well.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: buttermilk chocolate bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, combine sugar and margarine; blend thoroughly.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in buttermilk. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt and soda.
Stir just until dry particles are moistened. Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove from pan, cool completely and slice.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Make your favorite pie crust.
Mix apples, sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Put in pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Make crumbs for on top (mix flour, sugar and water); sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for almost 1 hour.

title: christmas cake
directions: Mix spice cake mix, shortening and boiling water.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Beat and add 2 eggs and sherry.
Combine the chopped fruit, raisins and nuts.
Stir into batter.
Bake in greased and paper lined loaf or tube pan until done at 300°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In large cake pan, pour peaches and water.
In small bowl, mix sugar and flour.
Pour mix over peaches and spread.
Add box of cake mix on top, spreading evenly.
Cut up stick of margarine and spread over top.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Cook noodles.
Stir in butter, cream and cheese while noodles are hot.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream margarine with peanut butter.
Add vanilla and sugar. Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate bits with paraffin wax.
Using a toothpick, dip each ball into chocolate mixture and lay it on wax paper to dry.

title: almond pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, sugar, eggs, corn syrup, salt and vanilla extract in a bowl.
Beat until well mixed. Fold in almonds and turn into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: egg brunch
directions: Mix milk, salt and dry mustard together and add to the eggs. Put bread in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add cheese and sausage in layers.
Pour egg mixture over the top and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt cheese with milk on top of stove in heavy saucepan or double boiler.
Next, add sausage to cheese mixture and then add green chilies.
Let simmer for 20 minutes on low heat.
May have to add some more milk if it is too thick.
Serve over nachos.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Blend oatmeal in blender to a fine powder.
Cream butter and both sugars, eggs, and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add chips, candy, and nuts.
Bake for 6 minutes at 375°.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until almost tender. Drain and cool. Peel and slice into thick pieces. Make syrup of light brown sugar, maple syrup, sugar, butter, water, and salt. Boil slowly about 10 minutes. Cover bottom of large, shallow baking dish with half of the sweet potato slices. Cover with half of the syrup. Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour, basting occasionally. A topping of marshmallows and pecans may be added before removing from oven.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine milk, soup, salt, pepper, beans and 1/2 can of onions. Mix well and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased 2-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350°.
Good make ahead vegetable for holiday dinners.

title: cheesy rotini
directions: Prepare rotini according to package directions and drain.
In skillet, cook ground beef, chopped green pepper and onion until beef is done.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes, bouillon, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in milk, Ricotta cheese, 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese and rotini. Pour into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken normandy
directions: Mix stuffing, margarine and water lightly.
Put half in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chicken, onions, mayonnaise and salt.
Put in the pan over bread mixture.
Top with remaining bread mixture.
Beat 2 eggs slightly and add 1 1/2
cups milk. Pour evenly over bread mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking.
Spread 1 can mushroom soup over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Drain tomatoes and puree in food processor.
Save liquid for spaghetti sauce.
Wash and seed peppers.
Process fine with carrot and onion.
Add pepper to tomatoes with 3/4 cup white or apple cider vinegar, celery seed, cumin seed, garlic powder, curry powder, parsley and 2 rounded tablespoonfuls of salt.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press the rolls into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes; let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, salad dressing and Ranch dressing.
Cut all vegetables fine; seed tomatoes.
Put cream cheese mixture on rolls; press vegetables into cheese. Top with grated cheese.
Chill.
Other vegetables may be substituted.

title: dry rib seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using heaping measures.
This will make 12 ounces.
It should be sprinkled generously on spareribs before cooking.

title: deep butter cake
directions: Mix together first four ingredients by hand.
Pour into lightly greased and floured pan.
Then blend together last three ingredients; pour over top of cake mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add the butter to graham cracker crumbs in a bowl.
Place the mixture into a rectangular baking pan.
Sprinkle the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips all over the crumbs. Spread the coconut over the mixture.
Lastly, sprinkle the nuts over everything.
Finally, pour the Eagle Brand milk all over the pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mexicana brunch pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into a well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake about 20 minutes or until set.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion.
Add the next 7 ingredients to the hamburger, sausage and onion.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheese.
Repeat 2 times.
Pour 3 cups water on top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cover for first hour. Fits in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can be frozen.

title: chocolate peanut butter surprise
directions: You will also need toothpicks and aluminum foil.

title: creamed tuna on toast
directions: Take flour or cornstarch and about 1 tablespoon of milk and mix together to make a creamy paste.
Set aside.
Bring milk, onion flakes, celery flakes, salt and pepper to a boil.
Add paste to make a gravy.
Drain tuna.
When gravy begins to thicken, add tuna and margarine.
Pour over toast.

title: ground beef and cabbage
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and drain off excess fat.
Add onion, bell pepper and bacon cut into pieces.
Cook until slightly tender.
Add the remaining ingredients with the cabbage last and cook for 20 minutes over medium to low heat or until cabbage is semi-tender.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cornbread mix.
Mix well. Then mix cornbread mix and mix well.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: perfect peppermint patties
directions: In a bowl, combine first four ingredients. Add milk and mix well. Roll into 1-inch balls and place on a waxed paper lined cookie sheet. Chill for 20 minutes. Flatten with the bottom of a glass to 1/4-inch. Chill for 30 minutes. In a bowl, melt chocolate chips and shortening. Dip patties in chocolate mixture. Place on wax paper to harden.

title: quick cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Mark with fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: hot yeast rolls
directions: Add sugar and salt to milk while hot.
Add all liquids together and add flour and milk real good.
Let raise until double and then punch down; roll out about 1/2-inch thick.
Let raise again.
Cover with dish towel until ready to bake.
Bake at 400° until brown and then butter the top.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the butter or margarine and peanut butter together.
Add sugar, egg and vanilla; mix well. Sift dry ingredients together and add gradually to creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips. Form dough into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Flatten slightly with a fork.
Bake for 9 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Allow to cool for 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet. Serves 40. Time:
Do ahead or day before.

title: oven fried okra
directions: Prepare okra as if to fry.
Heat oven to 425°.
Using a long baking pan, put 1/2 teaspoon bacon drippings and 2 1/2 teaspoons cooking oil in baking pan.
Place in hot oven until oil is hot.

title: pineapple cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a large casserole dish.
Mix flour, milk and sugar.
Pour into melted butter.
Pour pineapple (undrained) into batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Open can of crescent rolls.
Press 1/2 together on bottom of cookie sheet.
Put block of cheese in middle.
Press other 1/2 of crescent roll onto top and seal edges.
Bake according to roll temperature.
May need to stay in oven until brown.
Serve immediately, spooning preserves around block of cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Brown in hot cooking oil. Remove chicken from pot and add flour.
Stir until roux is light brown.
Add onions and cook until wilted.
Add chicken and 1 quart of water.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Season with Tony Chachere seasoning.

title: mary miller's orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Oil your fingers, roll mixture into small balls.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Quick, easy and delicious.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients until clear.
Add jello and stir. Fold in prepared strawberries and pour into baked pie shell. Chill until set and serve with Cool Whip.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and salt, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake slowly at 250° to 300° for 40 to 60 minutes or until done.
Yields 3 pies.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Heat until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with egg whites and beat into meringue.
Bake at 325° until slightly brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries and orange in blender.
Mix with pineapple and sugar.
Let this set.
In another bowl mix Jell-O as directed on package.
Add cranberry mixture to Jell-O.
Add nuts.
Put in refrigerator to chill.

title: zesty italian pork chops
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish, arrange pork chops and pour in Zesty Italian dressing over chops.
Add 2 teaspoons white cooking wine and stir.
Season on top.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: grandma's nut candy
directions: Mix honey and sugar together in lightly oiled 3-quart saucepan. Cook over low heat until boiling.
Boil, without stirring, for 10 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Insert candy thermometer and bring mixture to 270°.
Remove from heat.
Pour candy onto wet work surface.
The mixture will be very thick.
Form into large square about 1-inch thick.
Cut into smaller squares with very sharp knife.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: don't brown the meat stew
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix tomato juice, wine, tapioca, thyme and salt in a 4-quart ovenproof pot or Dutch oven until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 3 1/2 to 4 hours, stirring once, until meat is tender and sauce has thickened.

title: old time mac and cheese
directions: Put water in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; drop in 4 single handfuls elbow macaroni.
Cook about 8 minutes; don't overcook.
Drain.
Add milk and Cheez Whiz.
Cover and let set until cheese is soft.
Stir; add salt and pepper.

title: cheesy tater tot hot dish
directions: Mix hamburger, onions, green pepper, some of the Tater Tots and half of the cheese together.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine milk and soup together and pour over.
Top with remaining Tater Tots and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter. Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour and nutmeg, beating at low speed until blended. Add buttermilk, beating well. Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until pie is set. Cool on a wire rack.

title: jello surprise
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add pineapple, egg yolks and nuts. Beat well.
Fold in well-beaten egg whites.
Place a layer of crushed graham crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pineapple filling, then another layer of graham cracker crumbs.
Then pour on Jell-O that is partly jelled.
Refrigerate after jello is well set; spread with whipped cream that is slightly sweetened and beaten stiff.

title: southwestern bean salad
directions: In bowl, with wire whisk, mix oil, vinegar, cumin and salt. Add celery, scallions and beans; gently toss to coat well.
Let sit 2 hours.
To serve, stir in celery leaves.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, zucchini, oil
and sugar; beat well.
Add remaining
ingredients, blending
together	well.
Bake
in
2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: crawfish fettuccini
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell peppers in margarine and butter until tender (do not brown).
Add 1/4 cup flour and blend.
Add parsley and crawfish all at once.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add half and half and 1 pound grated Velveeta.
Add chow chow and garlic. Season to taste.
Cook on low heat 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cooked noodles.
Pour in greased casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan and jalapeno cheeses.
Heat at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Parboil cauliflower for 10 to 15 minutes.
Combine soup, cheese, milk, onion and salt in pan.
Heat until cheese is completely melted.
Break up the cauliflower in casserole dish and pour sauce over.
Cover with a good layer of bread crumbs (preferably homemade).
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Blend well; add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add 1 cup crunchy peanut butter.
Put in buttered dish and cool for 1 hour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Fry onions, green pepper, mushrooms and garlic in small amount of oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer 2 hours.
Cook the spaghetti in boiling water 10 minutes.
Drain and blanch.
Cook until tender in additional quart of chicken broth.
Mix spaghetti with sauce and layer with spaghetti, chicken, sauce and cheese. Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top.
Heat through until cheese is melted at 350°.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and 1/3 cup water.
Add flour mixture, soda, salt and spices.
Mix until moistened.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin with water according to package directions omitting 1 cup water and substituting 1 cup strawberries and juice.
Add pineapple and juice.
Stir and put into glass bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: freezer corn
directions: Bring to boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Let stand and cool. Put in containers and freeze.

title: sprigg's cajun shrimp soup
directions: Melt butter in a large pot over medium heat. Saute green bell pepper, onions, and garlic until tender.
Stir in vegetable juice, clam juice, and water.
Season with thyme, basil, red pepper, bay leaf, and salt.
Bring to a boil and stir in rice.
Reduce heat, and cover. Simmer 15 minutes, until rice is tender.
Stir in shrimp, and cook 5 minutes, or until shrimp are opaque.
Remove the bay leaf and season with hot sauce.

title: pepper relish(cooked)
directions: Remove the stems and seeds from the red and green peppers. Chop vegetables in the grinder, using large blade. Pour boiling water over vegetables to cover.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain. Again pour boiling water over the vegetables and allow to stand 10 minutes.
Drain for 1 hour.
Add the vinegar, salt and sugar and cook for 1 hour.
Then put into hot jars, not cold ones.
Makes 6 pints.

title: pollo al limone(lemon chicken, 4 servings)
directions: Clean, rinse and pat the chicken dry.
Make a mixture of the finely chopped garlic, sage, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Stuff the chicken with 3/4 of the fresh herb mixture and the sliced lemon.
Tie chicken as you would a roast.
Rub the remaining herbs on the outside and between the legs.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Place the chicken in a roasting pan with the olive oil and bake until golden brown, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add the white wine and lemon juice and roast for 10 more minutes.
Remove chicken from oven; add
chicken broth and simmer for 5 minutes over medium heat. Remove chicken from pan and reduce sauce by half.
At this point, add the butter and flour to thicken and finish the sauce.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
Thaw pie crust for 10 minutes.
Prick bottom and sides of crust with fork.
Bake shell on cookie sheet for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce heat to 350°.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Dip chicken in bowl.
Place in pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine the rice with shrimp and crab meat.
Add pepper and mushrooms.
Add enough mayonnaise to hold casserole together.
Add salt, pepper and celery.
Top with crumbled potato chips.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: yummy dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill for 2 hours, allowing flavors to blend. Serve with vegetables, chips or Fritos.

title: pina colada slush
directions: Mix together well and freeze.
To serve, mix half and half with 7-Up.

title: grandma's lady finger cake
directions: Bring chocolate, cream, sugar and vanilla to a boil, stirring constantly in sauce pan. Add egg to chocolate mixture and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Place lady fingers lengthwise in a bread pan (loaf) and layer with chocolate alternating with layers of lady fingers. Refrigerate until firm. Serve slices of cake with whipped cream.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: seasoned potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Can peel, if preferred.
Slice potatoes, not too thin, not too thick, along length of potato.
Pour some vegetable oil over potatoes in a mixing bowl.
Be sure each slice is covered with the oil as you place slices on cookie sheets. Shake envelope of dressing mix, then sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake on 400°.
Check after 20 minutes.
You may want to turn potatoes and sprinkle with more mix.
Bake until potatoes are almost crispy on the edges.
Great with grilled chicken and salad!

title: country crust white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs, oil and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour.
Turn bowl of mixture onto a floured surface and let set with bowl covering bread mixture for about 10 minutes.
Knead mixture. Place in a clean, lightly oiled bowl.
Cover with clean cloth and allow to rise until a finger poked into mixture leaves a hole. Knead mixture until all air is out.
I let rise a second time in bowl, but if time is short it can be shaped into loaves and placed into lightly greased loaf pans at this time.
Cover with cloth and allow to double in size.
Bake in a 350° oven about 1 hour.
Top should be lightly brown.
When turned out of pan, bottom should sound hollow when thumped with finger.
Melt a small amount of butter over top.
Cool slightly and enjoy.

title: charlotte's beef burgundy
directions: Heat butter; saute onions and remove.
Heat oil and brown beef; remove.
Discard all but a small amount of oil.
Stir in flour, bouillon and tomato paste until smooth.
Add wine, beef, pepper, herbs, onions and mushrooms.
Mix and bake, covered, 3 hours at 325°.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: baked ham
directions: With a sharp knife punch deep holes in ham.
Push garlic cloves deep in holes.
Rub ham with black pepper and salt.
Cover ham with pineapple slices.
Wrap ham in foil.
Cook in moderate oven (350°) about 2 hours or until tender.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Melt butter and add onion, cooking until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat well; do not boil.
Serve over hot rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, evaporated milk and marshmallows.
Put in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook quickly to a boil and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and stir until dissolved.
Pour into buttered pan and cool in refrigerator.
Makes 2 pounds of fudge.
May add chopped nuts, if desired.

title: beirock casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and salt and pepper to taste. Drain.
Steam cabbage with hamburger and add soup.
Flatten 1/2 crescent rolls on bottom of 9x13 pan.
Put hamburger and cabbage on top with cheese.
Top with rest of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20-25 minutes.

title: cheesy bacon-stuffed potatoes
directions: Microwave the potatoes until done.
Let cool.
Remove pulp from potato shells.
Combine bacon, onion, cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and potato pulp.
Mix well.
Stuff shells with potato mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Place stuffed potatoes on a microwave-safe serving platter.
Microwave at High for 5 to 7 minutes or until thoroughly heated, giving dish 1/2 turn.

title: ann's hit or miss casserole
directions: Make meatballs and brown and drain grease away.
Layer bottom with 1/2 of the flour tortillas.
Add 1/2 green peppers, onions, meatballs and 1 quart of salsa.
Repeat another layer and top with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Top with sour cream and black olives.

title: salsa
directions: Saute the oil, onion, garlic and tomatoes in pot until done, then add the other ingredients.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Boil oleo and water.
Add flour and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and spread mixture in bottom.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: bee's oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/4 cup boiling water over quick oats.
Add butter or margarine.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Then add remaining ingredients into mixing bowl and beat approximately 2 minutes. Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.
A tooth pick stuck into the center of the cake should come out clean.

title: korean noodles and beef(main course from abroad - pungent dish)
directions: Other vegetables, such as sliced water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, snow peas, etc., may be added.

title: microwave one-step lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add sauce and mix well.
Spoon 1/3 of mixture into glass or Pyrex baking dish.
Layer uncooked lasagna, cottage cheese and grated or thinly sliced Mozzarella.
Repeat layers. Pour the water over all.
Cover loosely with plastic or waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes (turn once).
Microwave on Medium for 20 to 25 minutes more (turn once or twice).
Before the last 1 or 2 minutes, remove covering and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Leave cover off and bake.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla, then add the sifted dry ingredients plus chopped nuts.
Roll in small balls, about size of walnut.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or more.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from chops and render fat until 2 tablespoons accumulate.
Discard trimmings and brown chops in fat on both sides.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.
Saute pepper and onion.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, corn, kidney beans and uncooked rice and water, chilies, hot pepper sauce to taste and salt. Bring to boil.
Turn into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with pork chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar, cornstarch and jello.
Stir until thick. Cool 20 minutes.
Pour over top of berries which have been put in baked crust.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan pour in applesauce and pineapple.
Spread cake mix over this and add diced oleo. Sprinkle coconut and nuts over oleo and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Sift flour and salt together. Cut or rub in shortening until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle with water, mixing lightly until dough begins to stick together. Turn out on a lightly-floured board or pastry cloth. Press dough together and roll to a 12 x 18-inch rectangle. Brush with butter; sprinkle with cheese. Carefully fold 1/3 of the pastry over the center 1/3, then fold remaining 1/3 of pastry over center portion, making a 4 x 18-inch rectangle. Cut into strips about 3/4-inch wide. Arrange on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hermits
directions: Heat oven to 375.
Mix brown sugar, shortening, margarine, coffee, egg, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat all together and put into pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Roll and cut out dough on a floured cloth.
Grease pans with oil.
Dip both sides of biscuits in oiled pan.
Place in pan (sides touching) and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Move oven rack up 1 step so the bottom of the biscuits will not overbake.
Makes 20 biscuits.

title: baked apple pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease an 8-inch square pan. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs. Stir in apples, flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Pour into pan. Bake 45 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream or Vanilla Sauce.

title: succotash casserole
directions: Melt oleo in long dish.
Pour over crackers and almonds.
Mix well.
Drain corn and spread over bottom of pan.
Cover with green beans.
Mix sour cream, soup, onions and cheese.
Pour over beans.
Sprinkle crackers and almonds; mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fluff waffles
directions: In a large

bowl combine flour, sugar, egg yolks, milk and oil. Stir until smooth. Beat egg whites until stiff peak forms. Fold into batter. Bake in a preheated waffle iron. If you want pecan waffles sprinkle chopped pecans over batter in waffle iron. Serve hot with butter and hot syrup.

title: onion nut dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cover and chill.
May be served with chips or raw vegetables.

title: orange cranberry trifle
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 tsp. orange extract.
Mix till smooth.
Gently stir in Cool Whip and cranberry sauce.
Set aside.
Using an 8 inch square pan, arrange 1/3 of cake slices on bottom of pan.
Mix together milk, vanilla and 1/2 tsp. orange extract. Drizzle approximately 2 Tbsp. of milk mixture over cake slices.
Spread 1/3 of cream cheese over cake slices. Repeat for second and third layers.
You will end up with cream mix on top.
Top with slices of almonds and cinnamon.

title: old time bread pudding
directions: Crumble
bread
in
greased
1/2-quart
casserole. Sprinkle with raisins.
Combine eggs, sugar, salt, milk, water and vanilla;
pour over bread.
Let stand 20 minutes.	Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted
in center of pudding comes out clean.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: how to get along with others
directions: Stir until perfectly blended.
Bake in oven at 350° for 5 minutes.
When done, put a pinch of sunshine on it.
Serve warm and share with lots of friends.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer on low in mini crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and set aside.
Prepare gelatin according to package directions.
Add sugar, pineapple, marshmallows, lemon juice and cranberries.
Mix well, put in refrigerator.
Stir frequently so ingredients will be well mixed.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix raw sausage and Bisquick with hands until crumbly. Add cheese. Continue to mix thoroughly. Press into a large ball. Let rest for 10 minutes. Roll into 1-inch balls. Bake on cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 350°. Drain and cool on paper towels. Store in the refrigerator. Reheat in the microwave.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: In a large bowl, mix the cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, egg, spinach, salt, oregano and pepper.

title: hobo stew
directions: Turn fryer to 250°.
Add onion, green pepper and oil.
Cook until onion is limp.
Add beef.
Cook, stirring with wooden spoon, to break up large pieces of meat.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Turn control on fryer to 220° and simmer about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tabbouleh salad
directions: Soak the cracked wheat for 20 minutes in cold water.
Drain and press out all excess water.
Finely chop the parsley, discarding the stalks.
Finely chop the scallions, including the green part.
Finely chop the mint.
Place the cracked wheat in a large bowl with the mint, parsley and scallions.
Add the coarsely chopped tomatoes and season with salt and pepper, the lemon juice and olive oil.
Chill in the refrigerator before serving.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine jello and cottage cheese.
Let set.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Broil chicken until tender.
Bone it.
Cut into bite-size cubes.
Put all ingredients into casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare chicken.
Boil, debone and dice into small pieces. Prepare chicken in desired seasonings:
onion and garlic salt, salt and pepper, etc.
Prepare 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Line bottom with stuffing mix.
Add layer of chicken.
Prepare next layer (soup, lemon juice, mayo and chicken broth) and small amount to next layer.
Add layer of broccoli and continue to layer until only stuffing layer left and leftover broth to top.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until hot all the way through.

title: onion party puffs
directions: Mix butter and soup mix together.
Spread mixture on the biscuits and bake in preheated oven at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rich cake
directions: Beat together and pour on top of batter.

title: angel muffins
directions: Grease muffin pan.
Combine all ingredients and fill pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve warm.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Immerse leaves in boiling water for 3 minutes or until limp. Drain.
Combine egg, milk, onion, salt, pepper, beef and cooked rice.
Place 1/4 cup meat mixture in each leaf.
Fold in sides and roll ends over meat.
Use toothpick to secure, if necessary.
Place in crock-pot.
Combine tomato sauce with sugar, lemon juice and Worcestershire.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover and cook for 8 hours on low.

title: coal miners cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
While cake is still warm, cover with topping.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together brown sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and water.
Pour into saucepan and cook over medium-high heat; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Combine all ingredients in baking dish; cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together; beat egg in.
Stir in applesauce.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Stir into flour mixture, alternating with water.
Stir in pecans and raisins.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When cool, make a meringue from the three egg whites.
Beat until fluffy, then add the 6 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat until fluffy.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together soup, milk and real mayonnaise.
Place in bottom of greased 8-inch square pan, layer of chicken, layer of broccoli and pour soup mixture over all.
Cover with any type of bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Put basil leaves, pignoli nuts, garlic and a little less than half of the oil in blender.
Blend about 30 seconds.
Add butter and 2 tablespoons of hot water.
Salt and pepper.
Gradually add remaining oil to thin.
Best served over egg or spinach fettucini noodles.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan or Sardo cheese, if desired.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry muffins
directions: Blend butter and 1 cup sugar until fluffy. Add vanilla and eggs until blended. Add dry ingredients and milk (alternating). Stir in berries and put in well-greased or lined muffin pan. Fill fairly full. Sprinkle sugar on top of each muffin. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Yields 12 to 15 muffins.

title: grilled amberjack
directions: Arrange fish in shallow glass dish.
Whisk remaining ingredients together in a small bowl.
Pour marinade over fish and turn to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap and marinate for 30 minutes at room temperature or 1 hour in the refrigerator, turning once or twice and spooning marinade over all pieces of fish.
Spray Pam nonstick vegetable oil on a clean grill and place fish skin side down, or place on foil.
Cook 4 minutes per side or when fish flakes.
(Cooking time might be longer on foil.)

title: roasted chicken
directions: Wash and prepare chicken for roasting.
Saute the chopped onions in the butter for 5 minutes.
Add the dried fruit and saute for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add seasoning and let cool for a few minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Pop popcorn. Melt marshmallows and margarine in microwave. Stir until butter is blended. Add some of the popcorn and stir it in. Add some of the cashews and stir it in. Add some of the M&M's and stir it in. Continue as above until all ingredients have been added. Put mixture into greased angel food cake pan. Let stand for a few minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce that tastes italian
directions: Microwave ground beef or turkey with chopped garlic clove until cooked through.
Pour off excess fat.

title: country supper casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in 10-inch skillet with onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour off any excess grease.
Place in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Pour over 8 ounces tomato sauce.
Add green beans and carrots.
Prepare mashed potatoes.
Spoon over top of vegetables.
Pour over 8 ounces of tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: theresa keen's baked trout or bass
directions: Cut fish crosswise, about 3 inches apart, on each side.
Chop onions in small pieces and also green pepper.
Place onion and pepper in each slide made in fish.
Place 1 tablespoon of green pepper and onion inside fish.
Pour the tomato soup over the fish that has been placed on greased pan and lay bacon lengthwise of fish.
Place in preheated oven at about 350° to 400° and bake for about 45 minutes or until tender and slightly brown.

title: peanut-butter and jelly surprise muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Line a muffin tin with muffin papers.
In a large bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, mix the peanut butter with the egg.
Add the milk, a little at a time, then add the butter and mix.
Pour the wet batter into the bowl with the dry ingredients and stir gently to combine.
The batter will be stiff.
Put a heaping tablespoonful of batter or enough to fill each cup about 2/3 full. Spread the batter gently until no jelly is visible.
Bake for 20 minutes, then cool on a wire rack for at least 10 minutes (the jelly centers can get hot).
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken and pasta skillet casserole
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, combine soup, milk and mustard.
On medium heat, heat to boiling.
Stir in broccoli.
Return to boiling, then reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 5 minutes until broccoli is tender.
Stir in pasta and chicken and heat thoroughly.
Serve.

title: hot pear soup
directions: Simmer leeks and butter, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add pears and wine and bring to boil (until pears are cooked).
Puree all together.
Strain, if needed.
Add remaining ingredients to puree. Simmer until heated through.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients right into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Do not grease pan.
Smooth out dry ingredients.
Make 3 holes.
Put 2/3 cup cooking oil in one hole.
In second hole put 2 tablespoons vinegar.
The last hole put 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Put one cup water and one cup coffee (liquid) over this and beat with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mock caesar salad
directions: Put the garlic, soy sauce and lemon juice in a salad bowl and whisk thoroughly.
Add the endive and romaine.
Toss to coat. Sprinkle with pepper and Parmesan.
Garnish with chopped tomato. Serves 4.

title: men-like-it-salad
directions: *According to color salad you need.

title: gourmet chili
directions: In large kettle over medium heat, cook beef until crumbly. Add onion and pepper; saute until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, water, tomato paste, chili powder, salt, coriander, thyme, oregano, wine vinegar, chocolate and garlic.
Simmer 2 hours or until thickened.
Add beans; cook 15 minutes longer.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Preheat 10-inch skillet over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Melt butter.
Add steak slices and onion.
Brown about 5 minutes.
Add bouillon cubes and water.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Simmer 25 minutes.

title: scented cinnamon ornaments(craft!)
directions: Combine.
Work mixture with hands for 2 to 3 minutes or until dough is smooth.
Divide into 4 portions.
Roll out each portion to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut dough with cookie cutter of desired shapes.
Use a straw or toothpick to make small hole on top of ornament.
Place cutouts on wire rack and allow to dry for several days.
Do not eat.

title: venison delight
directions: Soak venison for 2 hours in salt water and rinse.
In 12-inch pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onions and green pepper. Sprinkle entire layer lightly with salt and medium with pepper. Cook 5 minutes, turning occasionally.
Scrape vegetables into corner of pan.
Add pieces of venison.
Sprinkle medium with garlic and parsley.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Turn meat over.
Add tomatoes.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add mushroom gravy.
Stir until it starts to boil.
Shut off heat.
Serve over rice with salad.

title: wonderful pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except pretzels.
Spread pretzels on cookie sheet evenly; break into small pieces.
Pour mixture over pretzels; stir until all are "wet."
Put in oven at 300° for 10 minutes.
Take out and stir around; if pretzels are still wet," put in for another 5 to 10 minutes.
Take out and let cool for full flavor.
For more spice, add more garlic powder.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs, milk and oil.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder; add mashed bananas and other creamed mixture; mix.
Add walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown enough for you.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Bring to boil the water and butter.
Remove from heat and add flour; stir to ball.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat with a wooden spoon.
Spread into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat milk and pudding together well.
Add sugar and let stand until thickened, then add pinch of salt and condensed milk.
Beat well and add vanilla.
Beat well again and freeze.
Makes
a 2 gallon freezer full.

title: baked rice
directions: Turn oven on to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish. Cover and bake for 30 minutes.

title: arroz con porko(spanish rice with pork)
directions: Generously sprinkle Lawry's seasoning salt, then garlic salt, on both sides of the pork chops.
Sprinkle lightly with pepper. Place the pork chops in the pan and cook for 20 minutes until almost done, but not completely browned (usually four pork chops at a time).
Remove all pork chops from the frying pan.

title: ice cream
directions: Cook in a double boiler until thick. Mix enough milk to fill 1-gallon freezer. Mash the bananas and add to mixture. Freeze in freezer.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine pineapple, cheese, flour and sugar.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt margarine.
Add all ingredients.
Heat until cheese has melted.
Put into a blender to make it creamy.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl, then add wet ingredients.
Beat with mixer until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: hash pinwheels with cheese sauce
directions: Stir baking mix, water and margarine to soft dough.
Gently knead on floured board.
Roll to 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread hash to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Roll from narrow edge and cut in 1-inch slices.
Place on greased pan and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Serve with hot Cheese Sauce.

title: lasagne pie
directions: Cook beef over medium heat until browned.
Drain.
Stir in oregano, basil, tomato paste and Mozzarella cheese.
In a greased pie plate, layer Ricotta cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Spoon beef mixture over cheese.
Beat together remaining ingredients and pour over beef.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella or Parmesan cheese.
Cottage cheese can be substituted for Ricotta cheese.

title: spaghetti casserole(8 servings)
directions: Brown meat in a large pan.
Add all remaining ingredients, except spaghetti and cheese.
Bring to a boil; break spaghetti into the sauce.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Place in serving bowl; top with cheese.

title: best chip dip
directions: Mix together and let set for 2-3 hours.
Serve with chips.

title: chocolate chunk banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir eggs, bananas, oil and milk until well blended.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; stir until just moistened.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool on wire rack.

title: near year's pudding
directions: Make farina for 6 servings and add 3 to 5 tablespoons sugar. After farina is thickened, add the egg yolks and butter.
Mix well and set aside.
Meanwhile, beat the egg whites until thick and add 2 tablespoons sugar, a little at a time.
Fold into farina mixture.
Let cool and serve cold.
Top with Cherry Soup.

title: pepper steak
directions: Add beef to melted butter in skillet.
Sprinkle with garlic. Cook, stirring until browned.
Remove meat.
Add onions and green peppers.
Saute for 2 minutes.
Return meat to pan with tomatoes and bouillon cube.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, water, soy sauce, sugar and salt.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: plum cake
directions: Grease and flour 1 Bundt or tube pan.
In mixing bowl, combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Sift the flour and spices together; set aside.
Add plums to egg mixture.
Fold in the flour and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let cake cool for 1/2 hour and pour glaze on top.

title: christmas chicken
directions: Marinate all day or overnight.
Bake at 350° until done. Cover only part of the time.

title: au gratin bake dish
directions: Combine and bake
in casserole at 300° to 325° about 45 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
In another bowl beat eggs and fruit cocktail.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix by hand and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts before baking.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix with mixer the sugars, eggs, vanilla and butter until sugar feels dissolved (about 5 minutes).
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° to 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: diet baby ruth candy bar
directions: Mix together. Form into small bars.

title: green beans with garlic butter
directions: Cook beans in water until tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan; add garlic.
Drain beans.
Toss with garlic butter.

title: lemon roll
directions: Beat egg yolks (save whites) on high until pale and thick.
Add 1/4 cup sugar gradually.
Stir in oil and lemon extract.
Set aside.
Beat whites until foamy.
Add 1/2 cup sugar gradually until stiff.
Fold in yolk mixture.
In separate bowl, combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Roll cake up and cool.
Then fill and frost with the following:

title: marinated potato salad
directions: Cook and cube potatoes. Chop onion.
Toss all together.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.

title: cranberry crimson mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin; add to salad dressing.
Mix well.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in cran-fruit and applesauce.
Pour into 5 cup mold.
Chill until set.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Cream brown sugar and oleo.
Add flour and pecans.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan and brown about 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip; chill.
Pour mixture into crust and then pour blueberry pie filling on top.

title: skillet barbecue pork chops
directions: Trim off fat from edges of pork chops. Heat oil in a large skillet. Brown pork chops on both sides. Place chops in a baking pan. Top with green pepper. Make sauce. Pour over chops. Cover. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until chops are tender. Serve. Spoon with some of the pan juices.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornmeal.
Add melted margarine, eggs, vinegar and vanilla, beating after each addition.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in uncooked pie shell at 325° for 1 hour.

title: my sister-in-law's hot mexican dip
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft. Add tomatoes and jalapeo. Cook 2 to 3 minutes more. Transfer to a large bowl. Add the rest of the ingredients. Mix until well blended.

title: marinated green olive salad(insalata di olvia verdi)
directions: Place olive on cutting board
and
lay a spatula on top of each olive.
Smash down to crack skin.
Put olives, carrots and celery in a large bowl
with lid.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and pour mixture on top of olives.
Cover container and toss occasionally.
Serve
after
24 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Store in refrigerator but serve at room temperature.

title: fried catfish and hush puppies
directions: Hush Puppies:
Combine onion, buttermilk, 1 egg and jalapeno. Combine 1 1/2 cups cornmeal, the sugar, baking powder, soda and 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Stir wet ingredients into dry.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
When oil is at 350° add hush puppies.
Fry until golden brown.

title: chicken "chop suey"
directions: Boil chicken in 1 cup water for 20 minutes at medium heat. Add carrots in strips or slices, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 onion and 1/4 bell pepper. Continue to cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: mother's devil's food cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Cook sweet milk and chocolate	until
consistency
of	very
thick cream. Add to mixture
alternately
with
milk.
Add vanilla. Pour into greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake about 35 minutes at 350°.
Put together with Ideal Frosting.

title: mexicali chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in butter; remove chicken.
Add onion and garlic to skillet; cook until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients except green pepper.
Return chicken to skillet and spoon sauce over all.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Add green pepper and cook 10 minutes more.
Serve with rice.

title: hot tomato pickles
directions: Dissolve sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Add peppers, onions and tomatoes; bring to a boil.
Seal in jars.

title: lacy pecan cookies
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar gradually.
Melt margarine and add along with flour, soda and nuts.
Spoon onto large cookie tin, greased well, and spread to 4-inch round; space about 1 inch apart.
Cook at 350° for about 5 minutes.
Release with spatula. Quickly roll into roll.
May fill with whipped cream or cream cheese.
Enjoy!

title: tarragon mustard sauce (for fish)
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Put spoonful of sauce on top of cooked fish.

title: garlic-parmesan rolls
directions: Cut dough into 16 pieces.
Shape into balls.
Place on floured surface.
Cover.
Let rise 10 minutes.
In a bowl, stir Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and butter.
Roll balls in mixture.
Arrange loosely in a 9-inch round baking pan.
Cover.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken continental
directions: Blend all of the ingredients, except rice and chicken.
Bring to a boil. Put less than 1 cup of rice in 9 x 13-inch pan and pour hot mixture over same.
Place buttered chicken pieces on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender and brown.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, eggs, pickles, and salt, moisten with mayonnaise.
Serves 8.

title: white sangria
directions: Place peach slices, orange slices, lemon slices and mint in a large pitcher.
Add wine, sweet lemonade and liqueur.
Refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator, stir and serve over ice.
Ice can also be added to the pitcher when served.
Makes 6 servings.

title: butter rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
3/4 cup warm water; add 1 teaspoon sugar and
set aside.
Cream butter or margarine with 1/4 cup sugar. Add
egg;
mix
well.
Add yeast mixture, 1/2 cup warm water, salt and self-rising flour.
Mix well.
Put in greased bowl; cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: edl's turkey pie
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Saute onion and celery about 5 minutes.
Add parsley, mushrooms and sage; cook about 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/4 cup flour; cook until it bubbles. Gradually add stock; stir to prevent lumps.
Add cream.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Simmer 1 minute.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Reserve 1 cup.
Add turkey and lemon juice to remaining sauce.
Put in pie crust; top with top crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for about 35 minutes, until crust is golden brown.
Heat the reserved sauce to serve with pie.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Mix milk and yeast together and set aside for 5 minutes.
Then add the sugar, salt, butter and eggs to the yeast.
Beat thoroughly with mixer.
Beat in all-purpose flour.
Let dough rise for 40 minutes.
Mix in flour.
Cover and chill 1/2 hour in refrigerator.
Knead and shape into tea rings, coffee cake or rolls.
Melt butter; brush over rolls.
Cover and let rise 1 hour. Bake at 400° for 12 to 20 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine milk, lemon juice, pineapple, Cool Whip, coconut, nuts and cherries.
Mix well.
Chill well before serving.
Will keep in the refrigerator for a week.

title: peanut butter candies
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter and peanut butter.
Stir in sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of mixture into one-inch balls.
Place on wax paper.
Make a depression in center of each ball with back of teaspoon.
Fill each depression with 1/2 teaspoon of melted chocolate.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 5 dozen candies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream the shortening, vanilla, eggs and sugar well.
Mix all together.
Grease and flour 2 tin loaf pans or Bundt pan.
Bake at 375° for tin pans for 1 hour.
For glass or Bundt pan bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients together and top with butter Town House cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shell.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Cut 1/16-inch slice off blossom end.
Slice or strip, if desired.
Place in bowl, cover with 2 inches of ice cubes.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Drain.

title: perogies
directions: Filling:
Mix four cups cottage cheese with 2 eggs and 1 Tbsp. salt.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth. Serve with assorted fruit.

title: barbecued pork
directions: In heavy skillet brown the roast on all sides in a small amount of oil.
Place roast in a heavy ovenproof pan with tight fitting lid or a pan you can seal with aluminum foil.
Place the remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute; pour mixture over the roast.
Cover tightly.
Place the roast in preheated 325° oven and bake for about 35 to 45 minutes per pound. Baste several times with the juices in the pan.
Remove the roast and allow to cool slightly.
Slice the roast into bite sized thin pieces.
Add additional hot pepper sauce and few drops of vinegar if desired.
Yield:
10 servings.
Carbohydrate 5 g, protein 3 g, fat 3 g, calories 58.

title: snappy cheese spread
directions: Soften cheeses.
Mix all cheeses together well and then add pecans.
Shape into a cone and sprinkle with paprika.
Let stand a few days before using.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop dates, nuts and pineapple.
Mix with the other ingredients.
Mix together with hands.
Bake in tube pan or angel food cake pan (greased).
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Delicious!

title: steak marinade
directions: Pour ingredients into Ziploc bag.
Shake until combined; add steak.
Marinate several hours.
Cook steak as usual.
Great for London broil.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Melt butter or margarine over low heat.
Blend in baking mix and seasoning.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.

title: cream puffs(regular, sugar-free, cholesterol-free)
directions: Bring to a boil, oleo, water and salt.
Add flour and remove from heat while stirring into a ball.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until dark golden brown.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: cracker pudding
directions: In a 2-quart pan, beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, crushed cracker crumbs, coconut, milk and vanilla.
Cook until thick and put in buttered baking dish.

title: punch
directions: Boil water and sugar to dissolve sugar.
Add plain Kool-Aid and cool.
Add oranges, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
This can be frozen.
When ready to serve, add 1 bottle ginger ale.
You may use lemon-lime Kool-Aid in place of cherry and double the recipe if you like punch.

title: mayonnaise muffins
directions: Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.
May also be rolled and cooked for biscuits.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts and apples; mix thoroughly.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour glaze over cake in pan.
Let set for 1 1/2 hours.
Have glaze ready and pour on cake when it comes out of oven.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tested done.

title: pumpkin cheese roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs on high 5 minutes with sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Then add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger and salt and stir until blended.

title: jeanne's meat loaf
directions: Bake in loaf pan at 375° for 15 minutes or 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Place in buttered casserole.
In top of double boiler, mix the mushroom soup, mushrooms, grated onion, garlic cheese and sour cream, mixing and heating well.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs and almonds.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown.

title: raisin-bran muffins
directions: In a very large bowl, combine Raisin Bran, sugar and flour. Add buttermilk, oil, eggs and raisins.
Stir well.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
This recipe can be kept in the refrigerator for 5 to 6 weeks.

title: easy cornbread
directions: Grease skillet and preheat.
Mix corn meal, eggs, oil, corn and sour cream together.
Pour in preheated skillet and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: apple mold
directions: Bring 3 cups water to boil.
Add red hots, stir until clear. Pour over the jello and cool.
When jello mixture is almost jelled, add the apples, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into an oiled mold and refrigerate.

title: double pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar with 4 eggs.
Add pecans, oleo, dark and light syrup and vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry mash
directions: Cook sugar, marshmallows
and
milk 5 minutes, stirring often. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and cherry chips. Spread in buttered 9 x
9-inch
pan, or drop by tablespoons on buttered wax paper.
Melt chocolate chips, paraffin and peanut butter.
Add peanuts and coconut.
Spread over cherry layer.

title: corn and rice
directions: Fry pepper and onion in oleo until tender; do not brown. Cook rice until tender. Add corn, onion and pepper; mix in milk and egg, then cheese. Bake in casserole until bubbly at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: May use all ground beef.
Cook onion and green pepper in microwave until tender;
drain.
Stir together onions, pepper, tomato sauce, eggs, cheese, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, thyme. Add ground meat; mix well.
Shape into loaf in baking dish (9 x 13).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix and top with chopped nuts (pecans).
Bake at 300° until it bubbles.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: so good vegetable casserole
directions: Let frozen vegetables thaw.
Drain and heat.
Then add cheese and a dash of red pepper.
Arrange in casserole and sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend together in order given.
Bake at 350° in a greased tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Batter will be stiff.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2 quart microwave safe bowl. Microwave on high 7 to 8 minutes, stirring twice, until cucumber is crisp-tender and onion translucent.
Ladle into glass jar (rinsed with hot water to prevent cracking).
Cover.
Cool slightly and refrigerate.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl, except chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Then add chips.
Butter and flour tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: rice ala great
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add broth and soup. Pour into a quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Add applesauce, milk, oil, lemon juice, vanilla, butter and one egg. Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 375° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with diced apples, sugar and cinnamon. Then bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until apples are soft and a toothpick comes out clean.
Then eat it.

title: creole corn
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, cook until lightly brown.
Add onion and bell pepper, saute until tender.
Remove from heat and combine tomatoes, corn and seasonings; add to flour mixture.
Cook over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in oleo until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and stir over low heat until broccoli is broken apart.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: glazed nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heat oil and Karo in iron skillet, stirring to combine well.
Add pecans and stir, coating well.
Put this skillet into oven and roast, stirring every 15 minutes, until they are crisp.
(Be cautious not to overheat nuts; they can burn if you overdo it.)
Remove and pour onto waxed paper.
Separate nuts and salt.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add crushed wafers alternately with milk.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat sugar and egg until thick and foamy. Add dash of salt and beat in milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Serves 1.

title: crab cakes
directions: Cook onion in fat until tender.
Combine all ingredients except crumbs.
Shape into 12 cakes and roll in crumbs.
Fry in hot oil at moderate heat until brown on one side.
Turn carefully and brown the other side.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes.

title: dutch baby(this fluffy oven pancake cooks in a large frying pan.)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in a 2 to 3-quart frying pan or shallow baking dish.
Whirl eggs for 1 minute in blender, gradually adding milk and flour.
Pour batter into hot buttered pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve immediately with your choice of toppings:
powdered sugar and lemon juice, honey, syrup, jams and jellies, fresh fruit or heated fruit.

title: hamburger bean bake
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
Mix the rest and add to meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Mix 7-Up, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook on medium heat until it is thick.
Add about 10 drops red food coloring.
Put in another bowl; set in refrigerator.
Let cool completely.
Add strawberries and put in pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic in oil until wilted or soft.
Fry ground beef until brown; blend or mix 2 mixtures. Add cheese, cream of mushroom soup, chicken noodle soup, raw rice, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly and pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Stir ingredients and freeze for 24 hours.
Serve with 7-Up.

title: gerbish's wisconsin stuffing
directions: Mix all together very well and put into greased baking pan. Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake at 350 degrees for approximately 1 hour.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Place pretzels and butter in oven at 400° for 8 minutes.
Mix together sugar, cream cheese, Cool Whip, strawberries, strawberry Jell-O and water.
Make Jell-O adding strawberries and set.
Set until 3/4 congealed.
Place pretzels in dish, then Cool Whip mixture and top with Jell-O and strawberries.

title: homestyle baked beans
directions: Mix beans, brown sugar, mustard, ketchup, onions and bacon together.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Place bacon slices on top of mixture.
Bake in a 325° oven for 2 hours.

title: tomato soup
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Add other ingredients and heat.

title: double chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars, egg, milk and vanilla with electric. Whisk together flour, cocoa, powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: pancake sea prise
directions: Mix all the ingredients together. Shape into 6 thick pancakes and fry until brown on each side. Can top with a white sauce or creamed peas.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil pork until it falls apart.
Brown ground beef.
Saute onion and garlic.
Mix meat, onion and garlic in pork broth.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Cook (simmer) for 1 hour.

title: marinara on beds of spinach and orzo
directions: Cook orzo according to package directions; keep warm. Cook spinach in olive oil in a skillet over medium heat, stirring constantly until thoroughly heated. Sprinkle with pepper, tossing well. Spoon evenly onto 2 individual plates; set aside.

title: low-fat chocolate snack cake
directions: Spray 9-inch square baking dish with a nonfat cooking spray. In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, beat together wet ingredients.
Add to flour mixture; stir until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 16; .09 g fat per serving.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding; mix well.
Stir in the pineapple with juice and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Pour into serving dish and chill.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Add cabbage, onion, carrots and green pepper. Mix and sprinkle sugar on top.

title: "diabetic" coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar replacement, egg, flour and margarine in saucepan.
Cook and stir on low heat until mixture thickens and then remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Let cool slightly.
Spread over cake while warm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender and drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
After squash and onion have cooked and been drained, add other ingredients, except herb stuffing mix.
Use 1/2 stuffing mix in squash. Pour all of the mixture in a casserole dish.
Then sprinkle remaining herb stuffing mix over casserole. Bake in 350 oven for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini raisin cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Stir in zucchini.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except bacon. Shape into loaf.
Put bacon on top.
Bake 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: old-fashioned buttermilk pie
directions: Combine butter and sugar, creaming well.
Add eggs and flour; beat until fluffy (about 2 minutes).
Fold in buttermilk and nutmeg.

title: skillet chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and garlic powder.
Drain; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes and season to taste.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large mixing bowl, add sugar, flour and eggs. Stir; add remaining ingredients except raisins. Stir well. Add raisins and pour into greased and floured cake pan. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, flour, milk and water over medium heat until thick. Serve over homemade biscuits with butter for a breakfast treat.

title: chinese cucumber salad
directions: Stir the ingredients together just before serving.

title: tasty rice
directions: Stir lightly all ingredients; bring to a rolling boil and reduce heat to simmer. Cover with a tight fitting lid and simmer for 20 minutes. Remove from heat. Let stand covered 5 minutes. Remove cover; fluff with fork.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and 1 beaten egg.
Reserve 1 cup for filling.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and 1 cup of lemon cake mixture.
Put on first layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple and raisin salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Chill about 1 hour.
Serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
In another bowl, mix dry ingredients and add to above mixture.
Mix all ingredients and form in balls the size of a walnut.
Press flat on pan and bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions very thin.
Cover with ice water and 1/2 cup of salt.
Cover and refrigerate 48 hours.
Drain well.
Bring 1 1/2 pints of vinegar and 5 cups of sugar to a boil. Let cool.
Pack jars loosely with cucumbers and onions.
Pour vinegar and sugar over the cucumbers and onions in the jars. Seal.
Freeze.
Thaw in refrigerator overnight.

title: homemade yogurt
directions: Combine ingredients and strain into glass or stainless steel container.
Cover.
Keep warm (90°) overnight.
Blot off liquid with paper toweling.

title: warm cherry puff
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Blend milk, eggs, biscuit mix, sugar, extract and margarine in blender 15 seconds, or beat on high speed of mixer 1 minute.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan or 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Spoon cherry filling over the top.
Bake for 25 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: nutty-noodly clusters
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in heavy pan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in noodles and nuts so they are evenly coated.
Dip out by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill and refrigerate.
Yields about 24 clusters.

title: never fail microwave divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water on High for 12 to 18 minutes in a glass bowl (depends on your microwave), until it spins a fine thread.
In another bowl, add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff and if forms peaks.
Slowly pour syrup mixture into egg whites, beating constantly, until it loses its shine.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: mexican-style appetizer
directions: In a small bowl combine soup with taco seasoning mix and hot pepper sauce.
Stir until blended.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, oats and six tablespoons of margarine at low speed until crumbly.
Save one cup of mix for the topping.
Remaining crumbs, blend in egg.
Press into buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Take cup saved, add oats, butter, brown sugar and cinnamon; beat well until mixed.
Add pie filling; sprinkle mixture on top.
Bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: luscious chocolate bars
directions: Blend together margarine, sugar, egg, flour, soda and oatmeal. Keep out 1 cup and spread rest in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, using floured hand to push in pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: turnip casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook turnips in water for 15 - 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add egg, sugar, butter and salt. Mix well.
Transfer to a greased 1 qt. baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 20 - 25 minutes.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually, beating after each egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend with sugar-egg mixture. Stir in vanilla.
Add nuts and apples; stir well.
Bake in a 9-inch square pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: iness oliver's cheesecake squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine.
Press down in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 3 eggs and cream cheese.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Be sure to wash your hands before starting.
Wash and dry berries; set aside.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over warm (not hot) water.
Stir in oil.
Dip berries in chocolate, then place on wax paper to cool.
Do not refrigerate.
They may be prepared early in the day, but will not keep overnight.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk, egg
yolks and lemon juice with food processor.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Let chill overnight in refrigerator and top with Cool Whip.
For best results, crumb crackers in food processor.
Then mix with margarine.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, water, raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, cocoa and salt in large pan.
Cook over medium heat. Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool completely.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour and 1 teaspoon soda, mix well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all together and place in a greased 4-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This dish goes great with ham.

title: orange ambrosia supreme
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar and orange rind and refrigerate 1 hour.
In deep dish or bowl, place 1/3 of oranges and 1/3 coconut. Repeat layers.
Top with dressing, then pecans.

title: broccoli and orzo soup
directions: In large saucepan, heat broth and carrot to boiling over high heat.
Stir in pasta.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Stir in broccoli.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Beat eggs in a bowl, heat soup to a vigorous boil, add eggs in a slow, steady stream, stirring constantly.
Add cheese when serving.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until thoroughly mixed. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Pie comes out with pie crust and coconut topping.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In mixing bowl, blend potatoes, egg yolks, salt, butter and milk. Add 1/3 cup brown sugar and walnuts. Fold in beaten egg whites (stiff but not dry). Arrange walnuts and some brown sugar on bottom of large casserole pan that has been well buttered. Spoon the potato mixture over this.
Sprinkle some nuts and brown sugar on top of this mixture and bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: crunchy deviled egg salad
directions: Toss chopped eggs, celery, onion, potatoes, mayonnaise, mustard, salt and marjoram.
Spoon salad onto lettuce leaves.
Add tomato wedges.
Garnish with egg slices.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown onion and Crisco.
Add meat and rest of ingredients. Cook two hours or until barbecue is thick.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef lightly.
Add onions, potatoes, carrots and celery.
Add tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Add rice and spices. Then add cabbage and water.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: lemon squirter
directions: Roll the lemon back and forth on a hard surface (counter top will do).
Then poke a hole in the end of the lemon with the toothpick.
You now have a super squirter for fish, salads or vegetables.

title: fruit and veggie smoothie
directions: Mix all in blender until creamy.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix milk and marshmallow in a double boiler and allow to melt.
Remove from heat and allow to cool until mixture begins to thicken.
Add whipped cream.
Add chocolate to mixture and put into pie shell.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs if desired. Chill for at least 24 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese, crushed pineapple, maraschino cherries after cheese is soft.
Dissolve jello in boiling water. Let cool to room temperance, then place in refrigerator or until consistency of egg white.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Stir well to get all cream cheese lumps out.
Add Cool Whip last.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Thaw
Cool Whip.
Drain all fruit.
Mix buttermilk, dry pudding
and
Cool Whip together.
Fold in all fruit and nuts. Chill.
This makes a large salad.

title: lemon custard pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add dry ingredients. Mix thoroughly. Add lemon extract.
Add hot milk last.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until custard is set.

title: chocolate banana cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo and add eggs.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, bananas and sour milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Add hot water and mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: chewy crisps
directions: Blend well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool on pan a few minutes before removing.

title: chocolate chip butterscotch blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix flour, cake flour, baking powder and salt.
Toss brown sugar, sugar, egg, egg yolks and vanilla in a bowl.
Pour over dry ingredients and add chocolate chips and 1/2 cup nuts, if desired. Bake 25 to 29 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Mix juices, ginger ale and last add sherbet of your choice.

title: rice krispies peanut butter balls
directions: Bring sugar and Karo syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Add the Rice Krispies gradually to the mixture and stir.
Roll into 1 1/2 inch balls, Be careful because the mixture will be hot.
Place on wax paper.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in beaten eggs.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients and mashed bananas.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Chopped nuts and lemon juice can be added also.

title: pepperoni salad
directions: Cook rotini; drain and rinse with cold water and drain again. Combine salad dressing and mustard and set aside.
Combine pasta with all other ingredients.
Pour dressing mixture over salad and toss.
Top with Parmesan cheese if you wish.
Chill before serving.

title: tapioca cream
directions: In the top of a double boiler, mix egg yolk with some of milk.
Add remaining milk, 2 tablespoons sugar, salt and tapioca. Cook 8 to 10 minutes over rapidly boiling water. Stir frequently.

title: cream of watercress soup
directions: In a heavy bottomed Dutch oven over medium-low heat, melt butter.
Stir in chopped onions.
Stir onions until they are transparent.
Add potato, watercress and chicken stock.
Bring to a boil.
Decrease heat and simmer until potato is soft enough to be mashed against the side of the pan with a wooden spoon and watercress is wilted.
Cool mixture.
Pour into the container of a blender.
Blend on high until completely pureed.
Pour into a sieve and force through into a bowl, pushing the solids against the sieve with the back of a wooden spoon.
Be patient; the finer the sieve, the more refined the soup.
Pour mixture back into the Dutch oven which has been rinsed and dried.
Stir in cream, salt and white pepper to taste.
Warm through and serve.
Serves 4.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: In a mixing bowl combine flour and salt.
Beat egg with shortening and add to flour mixture.
Add water and vinegar.
