Mix well.
Roll out between 2 pieces wax paper.
Makes three 9-inch pie shells.

title: peach cobbler for two
directions: Mix first three ingredients; add peaches.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add butter and lemon juice; pour into 2 individual casseroles.
Add Biscuit Topper.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: vanilla cupcakes(serves 24)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 24 muffin pans with paper liners or grease pans and dust lightly with flour.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together into bowl.
In a separate bowl, cream butter; add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, one at a time.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk to egg mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain off fat.
Spoon beef into 8-inch square baking pan.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs.
Pour mixture over casserole, covering evenly.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
(Can be doubled for larger casserole.)

title: carrot salad
directions: Add carrots, raisins, pineapple and sugar; mix well.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Chill before serving.

title: heavenly brownies
directions: Melt chocolate squares in a double boiler.
Beat together softened butter, sugar and eggs.
Pour melted chocolate into mix and stir together.
Sift flour into mixture.
Add a pinch of salt and vanilla.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex (greased) pan. Sprinkle chocolate morsels all over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken mana
directions: Combine cream of chicken soup, canned milk and green chiles together.
Layer in a crock-pot the soup mixture, tortillas, meat, cheese, onion, soup mixture and tortillas, until all is used, ending with cheese.
Place lid on; turn to medium heat for several hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: coconut custard mochi
directions: Cream the butter, eggs and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: noodle pleaser
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream; set aside.
Brown chuck in margarine; add onions, garlic, salt, sugar, pepper and tomato sauce.
Cover and cook 20 minutes on low heat.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.

title: caramel corn
directions: Heat to slow boil for 15 minutes.
Take off stove and add 1 teaspoon baking soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix with 5 quarts popped corn.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 225° for 45 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes.
Pour onto waxed paper.

title: 9-layer salad
directions: Layer the vegetables in the order listed in a 2-quart dish or bowl.
Top with bacon bits.
Cover tightly and chill several hours before serving.

title: no fail chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a blender.
Pour in double boiler and cook until thick.
Stir from sides of pot several times while cooking.
Pour back in blender and add the butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
(Start with low speed and go to high speed on blender.)
Filling will become very smooth and silky. Pour into the pie crusts.
Filling thickens immediately.
Let set until cool.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: date filled cookies
directions: Cook dates, sugar and water over medium heat until thick and bubbling in a saucepan.
Add chopped nuts.

title: sausage-cheese biscuits
directions: Combine cheese, sausage and biscuit mix.
Drop on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown.

title: vegetable molded salad
directions: Grind ingredients.
Dissolve 1 envelope gelatin in 1 cup water and add to the ground ingredients.
Add salt to taste.
Put into individual molds.
Serve with mayonnaise on lettuce leaves.

title: bess' mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook potatoes.
Mash with cream cheese and sour cream.
Add butter and paprika.
Milk may be added, if too thick. Bake in casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pasta and bean soup(pasta e fagioli)
directions: Saute onion in olive oil over medium heat until onion is translucent.
Add carrot, celery and ham bone.
Continue to saute vegetables and turn ham bone so that meat is browned.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add beans and simmer for another 10 minutes.
Stir in broth and water.
Raise heat to medium-high.
When liquid begins to boil, add pasta and cook until pasta is al dente (firm to bite).
If soup is too thick, add more broth or water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove soup from heat and allow it to sit, covered, for about 10 minutes before serving.
Serve soup with a sprinkling of grated Parmesan. Makes 6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat with seasoning; drain meat.
Cut up lettuce, tomatoes, onion and pepper.
Mix in large bowl.
Add meat, cheese and dressing.
Place in pan and chill.
Top with broken Doritos when ready to serve.

title: individual apple dumplings
directions: Roll pastry 1/8-inch thick and cut into 6 large squares. Place an apple in the center of each square. Combine sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Place equal amount of sugar mixture in center of each apple.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Moisten edges of pastry.
Bring corners together at top of apple.
Seal edges. Prick pastry with fork or make gashes with sharp knife.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° 30 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: chicken venetian
directions: Arrange single layer of chicken in 10 x 13-inch baking dish. Blend other ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil. Refrigerate and marinate up to 4 hours or all day, if desired. Bake covered 45 minutes at 375°, then uncover and bake 15 more minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together.
Use about 3 teaspoons to a cup of water.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Whip cream in blender until soft peaks form.
Gradually add cream cheese. Stir in onion and shrimp.
Add garlic powder to taste. Serve with strong potato chips.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon in small bowl; set aside.
Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and sour cream.
Pour half of batter into prepared pan and sprinkle with half of cinnamon mixture.
Pour in remaining batter and sprinkle with remaining cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: happence soup
directions: Make meat stock from the ham bone, chicken backs or beef bones. To that stock, add the tomatoes, okra, celery, onion, carrots, corn and potatoes.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender.
Add meat off chicken, ham or beef bones.
Serve with cornpone bread or saltine crackers.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Fry desired amounts of bacon and onion.
Mix together beans, soup, brown sugar, bacon and onion with drippings.
Place in uncovered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Lightly
season
steak with salt and pepper.
Cut steak into thin
strips.
Saute
in
large skillet in oil over high heat. Add
onions;
saute
until tender.	Blend soups, sherry and sliced mushrooms with their liquid.
Pour over onions and steak. Reduce
heat,
cover and simmer 1 hour, until steak is tender; stir occasionally.	Serve over rice.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all items; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into deep hot oil (375°), frying only a few at a time until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: filling (stuffing)
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Fry onions and celery until soft. Add bread and brown.
Add eggs to mashed potatoes.
Then add bread to mashed potatoes.
Can be used to stuff fowl or put in a pan and roast.
Roast about an hour at 350°.

title: pecan delight
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add baking powder and beat more. Fold in vanilla, sugar, crackers and pecans.
Place in greased pie plate and bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Let cool; cover with 1/2 pint cream, whipped.

title: noodle fruit pudding
directions: Boil egg noodles in salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse in hot water.
Add margarine and set aside.
Mix together eggs, sugar, salt, fruit cocktail and raisins.
Add noodles to this mixture and stir.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven until set, about 1 hour.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Thoroughly
mix
all ingredients, then freeze according to your freezer manufacturer's directions.
Makes approximately 3 quarts.

title: baked donuts
directions: Add shortening, sugar and salt to the scalded milk; cool to lukewarm.
Add mashed potatoes and yeast that has been dissolved in the potato water.
Blend in beaten eggs; work in flour gradually.
Cover; let rise until light.
Place on floured board; knead until smooth.
Roll dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Bake at 425° until delicate brown.
Brush with melted butter.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar, white sugar or cinnamon sugar. These are very delicious.

title: butterfinger pie
directions: Combine softened ice cream, butterscotch pudding and 2 1/2 Butterfinger candy bars.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining candy bar and drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: Combine all ingredients except spaghetti in large skillet. Cover and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti, stir to separate strands. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes longer or until spaghetti is tender. Add more water if necessary.

title: nocha kabab
directions: Wash beef and combine with ginger/garlic paste, green chili paste, salt, and turmeric.
Add 1 cup of water and cover; place over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Turn down the heat and cook until the beef is tender and water has dried up.

title: poor man's sausage
directions: Mix and knead. Refrigerate for 3 days.
Knead and mix each day.
Fourth day set oven at 160° and bake 9 hours.
Turn loaves after 4 1/2 hours.
Use broiler pan.

title: 7 day coconut cake
directions: Mix and put in refrigerator overnight.
Use your favorite recipe for cake layers.
Keep in refrigerator for 7 days before eating.

title: dirt pudding(or dirt cake)
directions: Crush cookies until they resemble potting soil; set aside. Cream margarine, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth and fluffy; set aside.
Combine pudding mix and milk until well blended, then fold in whipped topping.
Gently fold cream cheese and pudding mixture together.
To put cake together in pots, layer 1/3 cookie crumbs, followed by pudding mixture, then 1/3 of crumbs, then rest of pudding, topping with crumbs.
Refrigerate 10 to 12 hours.
One-half hour before serving, remove from fridge and decorate with flowers, etc.
Serve with trowel.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pumpkin doughnut drops
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, nonfat dry milk, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed (or with spoon), beat eggs well; beat in shortening, sugar, then pumpkin and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, alternating with orange juice; beat just until smooth.
Refrigerate 1 hour or longer.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar.
Gradually add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with cold water or juice and add vanilla.
Grease pan with butter.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups brown sugar with 4 teaspoons butter.
Arrange 4 slices of pineapple on top of sugar.
Place a cherry in center of each pineapple.
Pour on batter.
Bake in 350° oven until toothpick comes out clean.
Turn over on platter.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Put egg yolks in a pan and beat.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa and milk.
Cook on stove top until thick; add vanilla and butter.

title: icebox muffins
directions: Set aside soda water and buttermilk.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add and alternate All Bran, Bran flakes, buttermilk mixture and flour. Begin and end with dry ingredients.
Add dates, nuts or raisins if desired (I do!!).
Set aside at least 24 hours (1 week best) in refrigerator.
Can be kept in refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: southern skillet chicken creole
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in shortening, heated to 375°, until onion is soft. Add remaining ingredients except rice. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour and baking soda.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in yeast and sugar mixture and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly a few times.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Let rise in warm place about 45 minutes.
(Can make dough night before and refrigerate.
Next day, punch down, shape rolls; let rise and bake.)
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: spicy coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine cabbage, cucumber, tomatoes, green pepper and green onion.
Set aside.
In a small bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over cabbage mixture; toss gently.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, sugar and 3/4 cup milk for 2 minutes.
Add unbeaten eggs, 1/2 cup milk and flavoring.
Beat for 3 more minutes.
Pour in three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cake cool.
Use Seven Minute Icing and fresh grated coconut to ice.

title: waffles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg yolk and milk; stir into dry ingredients.
Blend in salad oil.
Fold in egg white, leaving a few fluffs.
Don't overmix.
Bake in preheated waffle baker according to manufacturer's directions.

title: white cauliflower casserole
directions: Wash and trim cauliflower.
Break into flowers and cook for 10 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Place into casserole dish and add salt, pepper and margarine.
Mix all other ingredients together, except Swiss cheese and add to casserole.
If you use sour cream, do not use flour.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top of casserole and bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add Karo, sugar, oleo, vanilla, salt and pecans. Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients to hard ball stage when tested in cold water.
Pour over beaten egg whites; beat well and continue to beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Melt butterscotch, margarine and marshmallows in microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes until melted and stir well.
Add pecan pieces and Rice Krispies.
Stir all together.
Can be dropped by teaspoonful onto wax paper like cookies.
Refrigerate until firm. Can be pressed onto greased cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch pan and smoothed by hand or with a rolling pin.
Cut into squares when firm.
This was served at our first after Chapel Egg Nog Party on Christmas Eve 1994.

title: brown rice
directions: Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: enchilada bake
directions: Cook beef and onion until done and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, basil, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Place 2 to 3 tablespoons of meat mixture in center of each tortilla.
Roll each tortilla to enclose filling and place in 2-quart oblong dish.
Pour remaining meat mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese over top and cover with foil.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbling.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: mock wild rice
directions: Combine rice, celery, onion, green pepper and butter in a skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until rice is lightly browned, then stir in salt, monosodium glutamate, pepper and chicken bouillon.
Heat to a boil, then reduce heat to very low and cover tightly.
Cook 30 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Just before serving, stir in 1/2 cup chopped filberts which have been sauteed in a little butter.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix and allow to marinate overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, including 1/4 cup melted butter. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: walnut balls
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and roll into balls. Chill.
Melt the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls.

title: hot wine punch
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil.
Keep hot in Corning Ware coffee pot with basket removed or any stainless steel pot.
Serve in cups with an orange slice.
This is a really good hot drink.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix together cocoa, sugar, eggs, evaporated milk, margarine and vanilla over lot heat stirring slowly.
Add nuts and coconut lastly after mixture begins to get thick.
Pour into pie shells. Bake 325° for 40-50 minutes.
If preferred you may put pecan halves on top of the pie before baking.
Makes 2 pies.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together adding 1 can of milk to soup and season to taste.
Add more milk if needed to get it right.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: squash bake meal
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Cool enough to cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds.
Fill with ground beef browned with onion, tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Top with slice of cheese. Cook in oven until cheese melts.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute
onions and pepper in bacon grease.
Mix in other ingredients,
except
rice	and
heat for 10 minutes, or until tomatoes
are
cooked.
Stir in rice and crumble bacon on top. Makes a large amount.
Delicious!

title: southern style rice
directions: Prepare rice as label directs.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, heat sausage links and water to a boil. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove cover; continue cooking.
Turn sausage links frequently until water evaporates.
Remove sausage links to paper towel and drain.
Dice sausage links.
In drippings remaining in skillet over medium heat, cook red and green peppers until tender.
Stir occasionally. Stir in rice, sausage links, chopped tomato and salt to taste.
Heat through.

title: punch base
directions: The ingredients make 1 quart of punch base.
Add 5 parts of lemon-lime, ginger ale, or whichever carbonated drink you prefer. Can be diluted with water, or can dilute with combination of both, depending upon what you are serving.
Can be frozen ahead of time. Thaws quickly.
Pour over ice.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and wash potatoes.
Chop very fine and put in pan.
Add very fine chopped onion and celery.
Add salt and pepper to taste and oleo.
Cook until tender.

title: bourbon street chowder
directions: In large heavy pan, cook shrimp with onion, garlic and bay leaf in oleo until just tender.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry orange punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine cranberry juice, ReaLemon and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, add orange soda, liqueur, if desired, and ice.
Garnish.

title: easy eggplant lasagna
directions: Boil until crisp-tender the eggplant and onion.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce. Layer:
lasagna noodles, eggplant sauce and Mozzarella cheese. End with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly around edges.

title: baked cavatelli
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
In a large skillet, cook sausage until no pink remains. Remove from skillet; drain off fat, reserving 1 tablespoon.
Cook green onions and garlic in reserved drippings until tender.

title: eileen's custard rice pudding
directions: Mix rice, 4 c. milk, 1/2 tsp. salt, and 1/2 c. sugar.
Slowly cook in heavy saucepan, stirring often, until rice is tender.
Add vanilla and raisins.
Pour into 2 qt. dish or rectangle baking dish (9 x 2 x 15 inches), lightly greased.
Pour 1 c. cold milk over rice mixture.
DO NOT STIR.
Scald 3 c. milk.
Beat together eggs, 1/2 c. sugar, 1 tsp. vanilla, and 1/2 tsp. salt in separate bowl.
Add scalded milk gradually to egg mixture.
Pour carefully over rice.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in pan of cold water at 325 degrees until pudding is set (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add beaten egg and applesauce. Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices and add; beat.
Then add nuts and raisins.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan, pour batter in.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or so until the cake tests done.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Add buttermilk, melted butter and blueberries.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: social security cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Mix all together except Rice Krispies and nuts. Bring to a boil, cook until thickens, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies and nuts, mix until coated. Make into balls and roll in coconut.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer.
Stir in hot water, slowly.
(Batter will be very thin.)
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch or three 8-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Frost with chocolate icing.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together all ingredients and pour into Oreo crumb crusts.
Makes 2 pies.
Chill overnight or place in freezer.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix eggs, crumbs, half of tomato sauce and rest of dry ingredients.
Pack into a 1-pound loaf pan. Pour rest of tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Place chicken in cooking bag.
Add salsa and flour.
Mix well. Add sliced green pepper.
Cook on 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and vanilla; add eggs one at a time. Sift together the
flour,
salt	and
soda
and	add
to sugar mixture. Fold in apples, nuts and coconut.	Pour into greased and
floured tube
pan	and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: mint chocolate cookie drops
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese slowly, stir until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour in mold and refrigerate for 24 hours. Take out of mold.
Serve with crackers.

title: sauerkraut cake with mocha frosting
directions: Grease and flour two 8-inch round cake pans.
On wax paper sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
In a large mixing bowl cream butter and sugar.
Thoroughly beat in eggs, one at a time, and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients, alternating with water until smooth.
Begin and end with dry.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Turn into pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes. Turn out on rack to cool.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix oleo and cracker crumbs for first layer.

Whip together egg whites, oleo and powdered sugar and spread over first layer. Pour pineapple next and slice bananas lengthwise over pineapple. Spread Cool Whip over bananas, garnish with cherries and pecans (use large rectangular pan).

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put all the fruit in blender or grind.
Add sugar and mix well.

title: tootsie reep tea
directions: Add cooled tea to sugar and lemon juice, then add 1 cup pineapple or orange juice.
Add 5 cups cold water.
Serve over ice with a sprig of mint.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; add cornbread mix.
Melt butter; add to eggs and cornbread mix.
Add onion, cheese and broccoli.
Bake in black skillet at 350° until brown.

title: christina straley's gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg and molasses. Then add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add hot water.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in greased shallow pan 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 15 portions.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix together 1 stick margarine and 2 cups graham cracker crumbs.
Put in pan.
Set in refrigerator and chill some.

title: riverview quail
directions: Salt and pepper birds; flour lightly.
Brown on top of stove in 1 stick of butter.
Add small amount of water, Worcestershire sauce, dash of garlic salt and lemon slices.
Cover roaster and cook in oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Baste often.
Add more water if necessary for gravy.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: Line 9-inch spring-form pan (sides first); fill in holes. Beat cream and confectioners sugar in bowl; set aside.
Melt chocolate chips and add instant coffee; blend well.
Add beaten eggs and yolks.
Add rum and beat with electric beater.
Fold chocolate mixture into cream mixture.
Pour into pan and refrigerate.

title: miniature christmas fruitcakes
directions: In a saucepan, combine molasses, water and vanilla. Add raisins and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in candied fruit. Cool.

title: paul's pumpkin bars
directions: In mixer, beat together eggs, sugar and pumpkin until light and fluffy.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mix. Bake in greased and floured pan for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Add first 3 three ingredients, mix well.
Then add rest of ingredients; mix all together.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Bake some and store rest of batter in refrigerator.
Will last for 6 weeks.

title: jane mueck's "johnny mazetti casserole"
directions: Saute meat.
Add vegetables and saute until soft.
Add soup and 1/2 of the grated cheese.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Cook noodles. Put noodles and meat and vegetable mixture in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes in oven at 350°.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook beans in water 1-inch above beans until tender.
Add tomatoes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix all together in order given.

title: reese cup pie
directions: Mix crumbs and oleo thoroughly.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Prepare pudding mix according to package directions.
Stir peanut butter into hot liquid, stirring until pudding boils, then pour into cooled pie crust.
Chill.
Top each serving with 2 tablespoons Dream Whip.

title: c. b. chicken casserole
directions: Cook onions and celery in butter until tender, but not brown. Stir in mushrooms, pimentos, chicken and cooked rice.
Blend broth and soup.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Turn into a greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into pieces.
Layer in order as recipe lists; mix mayonnaise with sugar and spread on top.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: squash casserole
directions: To cooked squash, add carrot, onion, soup and sour cream.
Mix seasoning packet and bread cubes in dressing together.
Pour melted margarine over dressing and mix well.
Add 1/2 of dressing to squash mixture and spoon into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle remaining dressing over top of casserole.
Bake, covered, in a 7 x 11-inch casserole at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy eggs benedict
directions: Blend soup and milk; heat. Place slice of ham on each slice of toast/muffin half. Top with poached egg. Pour sauce over eggs. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: mango bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well and add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Cook syrup, butter and brown sugar to hard ball stage.
Remove from heat; add and stir in 1 can Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over popcorn and shape into balls.
Lightly butter waxed paper and set out balls to cool.
Delicious!

title: cranberry cottage salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water in a small saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Stir in cottage cheese, cranberry sauce and salt.
Chill until slightly firm.
Arrange pineapple slices on lettuce-lined platter.
With an ice cream dipper, scoop out salad mixture and place a mound on each pineapple slice.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In large size bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven on 350 degrees for 50 - 55 minutes or until tooth pick inserted near center comes out clean. Refrigerate at least one hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: You can use your favorite fruits.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Spread rice evenly in a lightly greased 3-quart casserole. Spread vegetables over rice.
Pour chicken broth and water over the vegetables.

title: eggnog muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch) or line with paper baking cups.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Stir in eggnog, rum, magarine, egg and nutmeg, just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan.
Yields 1 dozen muffins.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter; pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, 2 eggs and box of powdered sugar until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: "no peekee" casserole
directions: Do not brown London Broil.
Blend all ingredients.
Bake at 300° in covered casserole for 3 hours.
Do not touch until 3 hours are up.
Serve on rice, noodles or with potato.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve chilled with crackers or breads.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: popcorn cake(kids love to help make this and eat it!)
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Melt the oleo and marshmallows over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth. Pour melted marshmallow mixture over dry ingredients.
Fold together.
Carefully press the mixture into a Bundt or tube pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Let the pan sit about 30 minutes. Turn upside down and "dump" the cake onto plate.
Cut with a knife into slices.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box. In a bowl, combine the cooked rice, sour cream, soup, chilies and salt. Stir to blend. In a buttered 13 x 9-inch dish, pour half of the rice mixture. Combine the cheeses and sprinkle half the cheese over the rice. Repeat the layers. Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Yield: 8 servings.

title: cranberry punch
directions: In a separate quart punch bowl, pour cranberry cocktail juice, frozen orange concentrate and ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add sherbet and orange slices.
Add wine and vodka if desired.

title: dilled green tomatoes(5 quarts)
directions: Use little green cherry tomatoes (or quarter small tomatoes). Pack them into sterile jars, scattering slices of celery, green pepper, dill and garlic throughout. Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil, then boil 5 minutes. Pour over vegetables and seal. Do not eat pickles for a few weeks as the flavor improves as the ingredients blend.

title: jello dixie lollipops
directions: You will also need 4 (5 ounce) Dixie kitchen cups and 6 plastic straws, cut in half.

title: fresh corn fritters
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder; set aside.
Beat egg yolks.
Stir in corn, pepper and 1 tablespoon oil.
Add corn mixture to flour mixture.
Beat egg whites until they stand in peaks; fold into corn mixture.
Drop from tablespoon into iron skillet containing 1/2-inch hot vegetable oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Yield:
1 1/2 dozen.

title: meat and tater pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes, salt, pepper, mustard and milk in large mixing bowl. Beat well.
Add ground beef.
Mix until combined.
Gently press mixture evenly in bottom and around sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Beat eggs slightly in small mixing bowl. Add potatoes, onion and parsley flakes.
Stir until combined. Spread potato mixture evenly in meat shell.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
While pie is baking, combine remaining crushed cereal with melted margarine.
Set aside. Remove pie from oven.
Sprinkle cheese evenly
over potato mixture.
Bake until cheese melts, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain off grease.
In a bowl, mix soup, water, cooked meat and onion.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese and then completely cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned potato soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown sausage pieces in butter.
Drain off all but 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add all other ingredients, except egg yolk, flour and milk.
Bring to boil, then simmer until potatoes are tender.
Mix yolk and flour, stir until pea sized and crumbly.
Add to soup, stir constantly, cook 2 minutes.
Add milk and heat through.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together pineapple juice plus enough water to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Heat liquid and dissolve cherry jello.
Let this jello liquid cool.
Add chopped mixture, cranberries, pecans, orange, sugar and pineapple. Put in molds or oblong Pyrex dish to congeal.
Serves 12.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together.
Let stand overnight.
Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: mandarin orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with pineapple, oranges, cherries and cottage cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add one egg at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add flavorings.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in preheated oven.
Do not open oven door while baking.

title: oatmeal apple raisin muffins
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing just until moist.
Pour into greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Makes 12 muffins. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve cool or hot with melted butter.

title: pizza chicken
directions: Roll chicken breasts in flour.
Brown in olive oil.
Pour spaghetti sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken on top, adding a alice of cheese on each piece.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Cut eggs in half and remove yolks.
Mash yolks and blend with mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Chop egg whites and combine with bacon, onions, potatoes and salad dressing.
Fold in mayonnaise mixture.
Season with salt and celery seed.

title: sweet onion muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl beat eggs, onion and oleo until blended.
Stir into the dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in muffin cups at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen regular size.

title: oatmeal peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl beat margarine and peanut butter with an electric mixer on medium for 30 seconds.
Add half the flour.
Add sugar, brown sugar, eggs, baking powder, vanilla and soda; beat until combined.
Stir in remaining flour.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
Drop dough from a rounded teaspoon 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: presidential cherry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9-inch layer cake pans, lined with wax paper.
Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in walnuts, coconut, carrots, pineapple and raisins.
Pour batter into the prepared pans.
Set on the middle rack of the oven and bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until edges have pulled away from sides and a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on a cake rack for 3 hours.
Fill cake and frost sides with cream cheese frosting.
Dust top with confectioners sugar.
Makes 10 to 12 portions.

title: jimmy's chili
directions: Brown ground
beef
with onion;
drain off grease.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: six week muffins(yields 70 muffins)
directions: Mix boiling water and baking soda; allow to cool.
Mix the shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Add All-Bran, Bran Flakes, chopped dates, raisins or prunes and nuts (if desired).
Mix well and add buttermilk, soda water mixture, flour and salt.
Bake in well-greased muffin tins for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: refrigerator potato rolls
directions: Cook and mash potatoes to make 1 c. of potatoes.
Set aside. Dissolve yeast in water and let stand 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, 2 c. flour, milk and next 4 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Place in greased bowl; cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours or up to 4 days.
Remove desired amount of dough and turn out on floured surface.
Knead until smooth for about 2 minutes.
Roll dough to 1/4 inch thickness and cut with 2 inch cutter.
Place rolls about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Brush with melted butter and serve.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Heat 1/2
cup
of the chocolate chips and the margarine over low
heat
until
melted.
Cool.
Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, vanilla, salt, eggs and chocolate mixture. Spread
in
ungreased
square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches. Bake 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows, nuts and remaining chocolate chips.
Bake until marshmallows are golden brown and wooden pick inserted
in center comes out clean, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely; cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 36 brownies.

title: chicken san marino
directions: Pound each chicken piece between two pieces of wax paper or foil to flatten slightly.
Cut cheese into strips, one per chicken piece. Wrap cheese in ham.
Place on chicken and roll tightly.
Secure with toothpicks.
Combine flour and salt and dip each roll in flour, then in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Saute in butter until browned on all sides.
Transfer to baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry dessert
directions: Blend yogurt, honey and orange juice together in a bowl until smooth.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Serve in individual dessert dishes.
Serves 4.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour over crackers.
Stir well and 30 minutes later, stir again.
Ready to eat.

title: praline crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange graham crackers in a layer in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Combine butter and sugar in a small, heavy saucepan.
Over medium heat, bring to a boil.
Boil for two minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in pecans. Spread evenly over graham crackers and bake for 90 minutes.
The topping will at first look "bubbly" and then will appear to "set." Do not overcook.
Place on rack to cool, cutting crackers in half with a sharp knife while cookies are still warm.
Store in a tightly covered container.
These will keep well for up to two weeks.
Makes 48.

title: party squash
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain and add all other ingredients except bread crumbs and margarine.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and top with buttered crumbs.

title: country style stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove tops, seeds and membranes from peppers.
Crumble sausage into skillet, cook with onion.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in rice, 1 1/2 cups cheese and tomato.
Fill peppers with sausage mxiture, top with remaining cheese.
Arrange in 9-inch baking pan, add 1/4 cup water.
Bake 30 minutes or until peppers are tender.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Boil sugar, salt, water, dill seeds and vinegar together.
In each jar place 1 dill head, 1 clove garlic and 1 bay leaf.	Fill jar with sliced lengthwise cukes.
Pour hot vinegar over all. Process in hot water bath for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate marble cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine cake mix and oil in large bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Press mixture into bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 22 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Increase oven temperature to 450°.

title: old fashion tea cookies
directions: Soften oleo.
Mix all ingredients and add flour.
Put in shaped rolls and chill or freeze and then slice.
Bake at 300°.

title: velvet crumb cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or round pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Beat all ingredients, except topping, on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 4 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sweet and sour chicken(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Dip pieces of meat (chicken, pork or shrimp) in beaten egg; roll in flour. Sprinkle with garlic salt. Brown in frying pan. Lay 1 layer in baking dish. Heat sauce in pan and bring right before boiling point. Pour sauce over meat. Add pineapple on top. Bake at 350° 45 minutes (chicken), 30 minutes (pork, small pieces), 15 to 20 minutes (shrimp)

title: diet (nood-less) lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium size nonstick skillet, saute ground meat and onion until onion is tender and meat is browned. Do not add fat or oil to skillet!
Add tomato sauce, basil, parsley, oregano, garlic salt, pepper and mushrooms to ground beef mixture.
Combine well drained spinach with cottage cheese.

title: easy deviled eggs
directions: Hard boil eggs.
Cut in half; remove yolks.
Mash yolks with deviled ham and mayonnaise to taste.
Fill egg whites.
Top with sprinkle of paprika or piece of stuffed olive.

title: sweet sour carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hot dip (slow cooker)
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger until crumbled; drain excess grease.
(I put my meat in a strainer and run hot water over it to wash the extra grease off.)
In slow cooker melt cheese; add meats and salsa.
Makes a large amount.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked fish(microwave)
directions: In a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, combine butter, parsley and lemon juice.
Microwave, uncovered, at time cook (Level 9), for 9 to 12 minutes, turning fish over once with a large
spatula after 4 minutes cooking time.
The fish is done when the flesh comes away easily from the bones when flaked with a fork.
Let fish stand, covered, 3 to 5 minutes before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and eggs; cream well.
Add salt and soda; mix well and stir in mashed bananas.
Add nuts and flour. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Combine pudding mix and sugar in a large saucepan. Slowly add water, stirring to keep mixture smooth. Cook over medium-high heat, stirring steadily, until mixture just starts to boil. Remove from heat.
Cool to room temperature, stirring occasionally.

title: chinese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut each bacon slice in thirds.
Cut water chestnuts in half. Wrap each half with a slice of bacon; secure with toothpick.
Dip each in teriyaki sauce.
Arrange 12 in a circle on a glass or plastic cooking grill.
Cover with paper towel.
Cook on Full power for 3 to 5 minutes or until bacon is as crisp as you wish. Repeat with remaining appetizers.
Dip each in additional heated teriyaki sauce when serving.
Makes about 36 individual appetizers.

title: child's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine, in mixing bowl, the peanut butter, powdered dry milk and honey.
Stir in the peanuts and raisins or chopped dates. Sprinkle with the water.
Mix until well combined.
Press fudge into a small loaf pan. Cover and chill about 1 hour or until firm. Remove from pan; cut into squares.
Store in airtight container.

title: apple cranberry relish
directions: Rinse and drain cranberries.
Peel, core and dice apples.
In medium stainless steel saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, onion and apples. Trim ends from lemon, cut in half crosswise, seed and dice.
Add lemon, cinnamon, mustard seed, cloves and salt to apple mixture.
Place saucepan over medium heat. Bring to simmer.
Lower heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring every few minutes.
Add cranberries and simmer 5 more minutes. Cool and refrigerate. Makes 3 cups.

title: top of stove pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together and cook until thickened.
When done, pour into ready baked crust.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat shortening and sugar together until creamy.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat well, then add flour and milk.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: nancy's cajun baked beans
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Add 4 cans undrained pork and beans. Mix in remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: scallop salad
directions: Toss scallops with 1/2 cup dressing.
Cover and refrigerate to marinate 1 hour. Spread scallops on ungreased baking sheet. Broil until almost cooked.
Remember, scallops will continue to cook after removing from broiler.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup dressing with cilantro, chives and orange rind.
Add cooked scallops with cooking liquid and toss.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Place each serving with greens and orange slices.
Top with equal portions of scallop mixture.

title: light and easy cheese cake
directions: Cream the sugar and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add lemon juice.
Mix the lemon jello and 1 cup boiling water.
Set aside and let cool until syrupy.
Then add to cream cheese.
Fold in the whipped canned milk into the mixture.
Put layer of graham cracker crumbs into the bottom of a 9 x 15-inch Pyrex dish.
Spoon mixture onto this.
Top with more crumbs.
Chill well before serving.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Combine ingredients to make sauce.
For large amount, just add more of each ingredient to taste.

title: sausage bread
directions: Place loaves on greased cookie sheet to rise.
Meanwhile, brown sausage.
When risen, flatten out loaves and place ingredients on top.
You can layer the ingredients, or mix them all together.
Fold edges of loaf up and around mixture.
Seal and bake at 350° until brown.

title: oriental salad
directions: Toss slaw, seeds, almonds and crushed noodles.
Mix vinegar, oil, sugar and beef flavoring.
Pour dressing on at last minute. Not good soggy or leftover.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Preheat a large skillet, electric skillet or wok.
Add oil. Add beef.
Cook quickly, turning meat over and over until just brown, 1 to 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Combine stock or broth and soy sauce.
Pour over meat and set to one side.
Let soy mixture bubble.

title: crab corners
directions: Lightly toast muffins and set aside.
Mix together everything else.
Spread evenly on 8 muffin halves.
Cut each muffin into fourths.
Can freeze now on cookie sheet and transfer to plastic bags.
Place frozen pieces on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 425°
or 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Add potatoes, onions, carrots, and celery and saute until soft.
Add flour and cornstarch and stir well.
Add stock and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture has a velvety texture and thickens.
Add soda and cheese and stir. Season with salt and pepper.
Add parsley a few minutes before serving.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Slice yams into bite size pieces; place in lightly greased casserole.
Add apple pie filling; mix lightly.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top; bake, uncovered, for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: quaker chocolate oat chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in oats and chocolate morsels.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Blend all together.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Pour on salad and enjoy.

title: unbelievable cheese cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well.
Add 6 eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add egg yolks and cream.
Beat well. Pour into a spring-form pan.
Bake at 500° for 20 minutes and reduce heat to 200° and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes more.
Cool and do not remove spring-form until cake is cold.

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Put into a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat.
Spread over meat mixture and bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 375° to 400° oven.
May add green pepper or other vegetables if desired.

title: crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend cream cheese, onions, milk, horseradish, salt and pepper together, then add crab meat.
Spoon mixture into plate or casserole.
Toast almonds separately at 375° until light brown.
Place almonds on top of crab meat mixture and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve on crackers or toast.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, salt and peppers to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Set aside for 10 minutes.
Add Certo and 2 to 3 drops of food coloring.
Stir.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Skim.
Pour into jars.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake 1 1/4 hours or until top springs back.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift together the sugar and flour; set aside.
In a saucepan bring to a boil oleo, cocoa and water.
Add flour and sugar mixture gradually as you stir.
Add the eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured jelly roll pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave custard sauce
directions: In 1-quart glass measuring cup, combine sugar and flour gradually.
Stir in milk.
Heat 5 to 6 minutes on High, until sauce is slightly thickened.
Stir every 2 minutes.
With wire whip, quickly stir in egg yolks.
Heat 1 to 2 minutes on Defrost, until sauce is thickened, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill slightly before serving.
Yields 2 cups.

title: potato field lunch casserole
directions: Arrange potatoes in greased 13 X 9 X 2 baking dish; set aside. Combine butter, water and onion soup mix in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350 for 1 hour.

title: pineapple - cheese casserole
directions: Mix juice from pineapple with sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thick.
Pour over pineapple which has been placed in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over pineapple and sauce.
Top with 1 1/2 cups crackers and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corned beef sauerkraut balls
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and onions and add corned beef and sauerkraut. Mix well and chill. Shape into 1 inch balls - roll in flour, then milk, then the corn flake crumbs. Deep fat fry for 1 minute or until golden brown.

title: cream cheese crescent roll
directions: Unroll 1 package crescent rolls and lay in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar. Spread over rolls. Unroll other package and place on top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: don's chicken and dressing casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, put half of dressing mixture (stuffing mix, butter and broth) in bottom of pan.
Add eggs, onion, celery, milk and salt.
Mix and pour over mixture in pan, then add rest of dressing mixture.
Cover with cream soup; bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.

title: boiled ham
directions: You will need 1 large lardstand with lid, 1 large old quilt and lots of newspapers.

title: artichoke cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in a casserole dish, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve hot with dark crackers.

title: depression cake
directions: Combine and boil together first 8 ingredients and cool.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.
Allow to cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: vegetarian veggie soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in 3 tablespoons olive oil until tender.
Add V-8 juice, tomato sauce and 6 cups water. Whisk in stew seasoning mix.
Add green beans, tomatoes, corn, carrots and potatoes.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add lentils, mushrooms and salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes longer.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Let hash browns sit out about 30 minutes before mixing with remaining ingredients. Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour.

title: stuffed burger casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Combine milk and meat.
Spread 1/2 of meat mixture in 2-quart casserole or a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour stuffing over meat mixture.
Top with remaining meat mixture to completely cover stuffing.
Combine soup, Worcestershire and catsup.
Pour over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for Pyrex dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients; press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.
Makes 24 bars.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir these ingredients in thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Store in airtight container as soon as cookies are firm and slightly cool.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Prepare jello as directed on package.
Put in refrigerator until almost jelled.
Stir in blueberry pie filling.
Chill until set.
Slice bananas and put on jello, then sprinkle nuts over bananas and add Cool Whip on top.
Easy and good.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in 4 pieces. Combine 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a large Baggie.
Shake biscuit pieces, 3 or 4 at a time, in
Baggie. Set aside.
In saucepan, heat white or brown sugar, butter and 1 teaspoon cinnamon just to boiling.
Set aside. Grease a Bundt pan. Sprinkle nuts in bottom of Bundt pan. Drop biscuit pieces into pan. Top with warm sauce. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes. Turn onto plate.
Makes bite size cinnamon rolls.

title: ants on a log
directions: Cut celery stalk into 3 pieces.
Spread with peanut butter and top with raisins or chocolate chips.

title: honey chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken in shallow baking pan, skin side up.
Combine next 5 ingredients and pour over the chicken.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°, basting every 15 minutes until chicken is tender and nicely browned.
Serves 6.
Good served over rice.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Pour hot water over shortening and mix until soft.
Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Roll out 2 pie shells.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushrooms in butter.
Add soup and cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Combine broccoli with soup mixture and serve in chafing dish.

title: nibblers
directions: Mix together.
Shake and store in an airtight container.

title: picnic shoulder ham
directions: Mix all ingredients, except shoulder.
Put ham in crock-pot (skin side up) and cover with tea mixture.	Cook on HIGH for 1 hour, then cook on LOW all night.
Ham will be so tender you can pull it apart with fork.

title: cheese corn
directions: Mix.
Grease a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour and eggs; mix well.
Add buttermilk.
Mix. Add lemon flavoring.
(For best results, beat with electric mixer.)
Pour in shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add jello to hot pineapple and water.
Remove from heat and stir.
Cool and add other
ingredients
and mix.
(May add small amount of grated orange rind,
if
desired.)
Chill in 2 large molds.
This recipe makes 2 molds and freezes nicely.

title: crab quesedilla
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 4 flour tortillas on ovenproof plate or cookie sheets.
Divide crab, chiles and olives and sprinkle on tortillas.
Sprinkle generously with cheese.
Cover with remaining 4 tortillas.
Bake in oven approximately 10 minutes.
You want the tortillas soft and warm and cheese melted. Cut in 8 wedges to serve.
Makes 32.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients well until blended well.
Serve with any fruit.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender.
Drain and stir in soup, rice and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a covered dish.

title: herbed pork and apples
directions: Combine herbs, salt and pepper.
Rub over roast.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain fat.
Mix apples and onion with brown sugar, Spoon around roast.
Continue to roast until internal temperature reaches 160° to 170°.
Transfer the roast, apples and onion to a serving platter and keep warm.

title: veal and peppers
directions: Lightly oil 4-quart pan.
Brown meat.
Add tomatoes, oregano, thyme, cloves and cinnamon.
If thick, add some water.
Simmer 2 hours or until veal is tender, then add peppers.
Cook 1/2 hour more.
Serve over wide noodles.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: easy cream broccoli soup
directions: Saute butter, carrot, onion and broccoli, then add soup and milk. Heat through and simmer.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: For sauce, melt butter in saucepan. Stir in flour until smooth. Gradually add broth. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Stir in coriander and half of the chilies.

title: tropical salad
directions: Cook tapioca pudding in 1/2 cup orange juice and 1 cup juice drained from pineapple.
Add water to make a cup if not enough juice.
When cool, add drained fruits.
Add bananas, just before serving.
This is good with anything but especially ham.

title: christmas fragrance
directions: Add dry ingredients to water and simmer to fill your home with the fragrance of Christmas.
Keep on your stove for a few days, occasionally replenishing the water.
(Not consumable.)

title: denver potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Generously grease 9-inch pie pan. In medium bowl, combine eggs, onion powder, thyme, salt and pepper; beat well.
Stir in potatoes, cheese, ham and green pepper; pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Garnish with tomato slices. 6 servings.

title: chili dip
directions: First layer:
Slice half of the Velveeta and place in bottom of round casserole dish.
Drain tomatoes and dice up one can of tomatoes and place on cheese.
Sprinkle half of the Cheddar and one can of chilies.
Sprinkle with chili powder and garlic powder. Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: opal's cream torte
directions: Mix flour and nuts; add melted margarine and mix well.
Spread in a long pan and cook on 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool completely.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Mix together and place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: blueberry tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, mix baking powder, 3 cups cake flour and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Reserve 1 tablespoon corn oil spread for crumb topping.

title: curried fruit casserole
directions: Combine fruits and drain off about 1/3 of the juice.
Add remaining ingredients; put in casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
The flavor is at its best when baked a day ahead and reheated for 30 minutes at 350° before serving.
Wonderful with pork or lamb.

title: luscious pineapple squares
directions: Mix all but nuts and spread on bars.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Can do ahead and freeze.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil (but do not boil).
Place Fritos in bottom of buttered casserole dish. Pour chicken mixture over Fritos.
Cover with cheese and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple crunch
directions: Pour 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and water over apples.
Mix and sift flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add unbeaten egg and work into mixture until it becomes like bread crumbs.
Cover top with crumbs.
Melt 1/3 cup margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in 8 x 10 x 2-inch dish.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Make a marinade of the liquid ingredients and sugar.
Add chicken breasts and let stand in refrigerator a few hours or overnight.
Grill over hot coals until chicken is done.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook hamburger with onion and
drain
off fat.	Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 1/2
hours	at
Can	be made ahead and heated later.
Can be heated in microwave.

title: french beef slice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat, onion and bell pepper in a large skillet.
Add soups and heat thoroughly.
Cut top off bread. Remove inside of loaf, tearing into small pieces and add to meat mixture.
Pour hot mixture into hollowed loaf.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Cut in one-inch slices and serve hot.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamed cabbage soup
directions: Combine ham and onion and saute in 1/2 stick butter until tender, approximately 10 minutes.
In large soup kettle, combine 2 cups water, celery salt, pepper, soup base, 1/2 stick butter, milk and parsley flakes.
Heat mixture to simmering point.
Add cabbage, ham and onion.
Thicken with cornstarch and water.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, water and Jell-O; boil until thick. Let cool and fold in berries.
Put in baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream or whipped topping.

title: lemon fish fillets
directions: In a large skillet, melt the butter and stir in dill, thyme, scallion and lemon juice.
Add the fish fillets and cook 4 to 5 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Put fish on a platter; pour butter sauce from the pan over fish.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Add water and oil.
Stir with fork just enough to form dough ball.
Roll out on floured wax paper. Place in floured pie dish.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 crust.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Have ready egg whites beaten to meringue with 1/2 cup sugar, speed number 12 on electric mixer.
Measure into mixer bowl shortening, milk and vanilla.
Measure into sifter flour, salt, 1 1/4 cups sugar and baking powder.
Mix shortening just to soften, using speed number 3.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add milk and beat at speed number 3 for 2 minutes.
Then add meringue mixture and beat 1 minute longer.
Turn into pans.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: meat ball casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine and shape by tablespoon into meat balls.
Brown, cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: linda's strawberry pie
directions: Bring to boil until slightly thick.
Cool partly, then pour over fresh strawberries (you can use frozen) in cooked pie shell. Cool 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip, etc.

title: betty's swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread in enough milk to make it wet.
Add to ground beef. Add other ingredients.
Make into balls and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
While meatballs are baking, combine ketchup, pineapple juice and sugar.
Place drained meatballs and sauce in slow cooker and simmer for several hours.
Makes 50 to 60 meatballs.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Arrange chicken in single layer in 12-inch skillet.
Stir remaining ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and let simmer gently, turning several times until chicken is tender, about 40 minutes.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Boil liquid in skillet until dark brown and thickened, about 5 minutes.
Spoon over chicken.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs and pineapple.
Fold in 5 slices cubed bread.
Pour into casserole.
Bake covered for 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Peel potatoes and dice up small.
Cook until they are tender. Add margarine, salt, pepper and about 2 tablespoons cornmeal. Simmer for 15 minutes longer.

title: caramel devil's food cake
directions: Pour half cake mix in pan.
Cook 15 minutes.
Melt Eagle Brand milk, caramels and butter.
Pour over cake and pour remaining cake over mixture.
Finish baking with nuts on top.

title: caramel-coconut squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour and mix well. Pat into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, sugar, eggs, and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Bake in a 9-inch pie pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 20 minutes.
As cake cools, it will make a well.
Mix together the sour cream, remaining vanilla and sugar.
Spread on cooled mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° until set.
Keep refrigerated.
May be topped with any canned pie filling mix.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Mix milk, margarine and bread; stir in salmon, egg yolks, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites in a large bowl until stiff; fold in salmon mixture.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 hour or until puffs and turns golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: parched corn
directions: Put hot ash in pot; put in the kernels.
Stir until brown. Clean off ash with leaves or cloth.
Beat corn in beater.
Make soup by stirring large pieces in boiling water; cook until done.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add sugar. Stir until dissolved.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and garlic. Add mushrooms. Simmer 10 minutes. Stir in spaghetti sauce and bring to a slow boil. Remove from heat. Cook noodles as directed. Grease a 9 x 13 pan and add: layer of noodles, layer of
sauce, layer of cheese, layer of noodles, layer of sauce, layer of cheese, layer of noodles. Add remaining sauce and top with remaining cheese. Bake for 30-35 minutes, uncovered at 350°.

title: dar's party mints
directions: Cream well the cream cheese and margarine.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Divide into 3 parts and add candy oils (peppermint, spearmint and wintergreen) to taste.

title: enchiladas verde
directions: Blend spinach, soup, sour cream, chilies and green onion in blender until smooth.
Soften tortillas in microwave for 20 to 40 seconds.
Spoon tablespoon cheese and onion on each tortilla. Roll up and place in lightly greased 8 x 12-inch dish.
When tortillas are all rolled, spoon blended mixture over top of tortillas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: chicken fried steak and gravy
directions: Mix ground beef with salt and pepper to taste.
Form into 4 patties.
Crush cracker crumbs.
Mix with garlic salt and 1 tablespoon minced onion.
Beat egg, mix with a little water.
Dip each patty in egg mixture; then coat with cracker crumbs.
Fry in skillet over medium-low heat until golden brown.
Mix mushroom gravy by package directions.
Serve over hot steak patties.

title: mother's old-fashioned dried apple fruit cake
directions: Sift flour in a large bowl.
Make a large hole in the center and add other ingredients.
Mix ingredients with flour until real stiff, using lots of flour.
Pinch off a piece of dough about the size of a teacup.
Place on a floured cloth and roll with a rolling pin about 1/4 inch thick and cut with a scalloped pie pan or quiche pan.
Place in a 9-inch greased cake pan.
Flour hands to prevent stickiness and gently press to edge of pan.

title: wild turkey dressing
directions: Fry onions until transparent in the butter and then add the bell pepper, celery, garlic, clove and parsley, mixing constantly over low heat.
When cooked down slightly, add the remaining ingredients and mix in a good size bowl, moistening the ingredients with turkey stock to soft consistency.
Stuff the turkey with the dressing or cook in a separate pan.

title: cornflake chews
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, then cornflakes. Spoon onto buttered foil. Makes 3 dozen.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Cover baking sheet with aluminum foil as if you were fixing to wrap a present.
Smash ground beef in the bottom of the pan.
Top with potatoes, carrots, onions, bell pepper, salt, pepper and other spices (if desired) to taste.
Seal the foil so it will be airtight.

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and put juice in small saucepan.
Add sugar, flour and egg to juice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Cool.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix shortening and sugar well.
Add egg and milk.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to milk mixture, beating until smooth.
Roll on lightly floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.

title: fruit slush
directions: *Add appropriate amount of water indicated on can.

title: venison stew
directions: In a heavy 4 to 5-quart pan, fry the salt pork over medium heat until crisp and brown and have rendered all fat.

Transfer to paper towels to drain; pour off all but about 4 tablespoons of the fat from the pan. Roll the cubes of venison in the flour to coat them evenly, then shake off excess flour. Over high heat, brown venison in the fat 4 or 5 pieces at a time. As they brown, transfer to a plate. Add onions and garlic to pan, stirring occasionally until soft and translucent, but not brown. Pour in the stock; bring to a boil. Add bay leaf, thyme, salt and pepper and return venison to pan. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 hour. Add potatoes and carrots to pan; simmer, covered, 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in the vinegar; taste for seasoning. Sprinkle pork bits on top and serve at once.

title: italian sausage and chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil sausages until done. Fry chicken in cooking oil in large frying pan. Chicken should be cut into bite size pieces about 1 1/2 to 2-inches long and 1 to 2-inches wide.
Brown chicken with onion.
Add celery and green pepper.
Stir in 1 cup water and the tomato sauce.
Stir until well mixed. Add tomato paste and remaining water. Stir until blended.
Add spices. Drain water off sausages. Set aside to cool while sauce is cooking.

When sausage is cooled, cut into small bite size pieces. Add to sauce and cook for 30 minutes. Cook spaghetti enough for 6 people while sauce is cooking. Serve sauce over spaghetti with salad and garlic or French bread.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable cheese melt
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions. Drain off half the water, then layer vegetables, cheese, vegetables, cheese, vegetables and top with cheese in 2-quart casserole dish. Put in microwave on Medium until cheese is melted.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: jettie's biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour, salt and baking powder. Beat eggs; add buttermilk to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Add to dry ingredients and stir. Knead 20 times. Roll on floured surface and cut with round cutter. Put on greased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 450° oven.

title: pickled herring
directions: Bring sauce to boil, until sugar is dissolved. Cool. Pour over herring and thin sliced onions.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread bread in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer sausage, mushrooms, green peppers and Cheddar cheese.
In a separate bowl, mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be made the night before and stored in refrigerator.

title: clam spread
directions: Spread cream cheese in 9-inch square pan. Spread clams over cream cheese. Mix ketchup and horseradish to taste; spread it over the top of the clams. Serve with crackers.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve both packages of Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart
shallow dish and cover with marshmallows while warm. Let congeal, then frost with sour cream. Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.

title: super easy shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain well. Stir beefy onion soup mix and gravy into cooked ground beef. Stir in peas. Spray a 2-quart baking dish with non-stick cooking spray. Spoon mixture into baking dish and top with mashed potatoes. Dot potatoes with small pieces of butter. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, until heated through and potatoes start to brown slightly.

title: orange-ginger custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, heavy cream, softened butter and lemon juice in a mixing bowl.
Butter 6 (5 ounce) baking cups and break small pieces of candied ginger into bottom of each cup.
Pour egg mixture on top.
Divide orange sections and place on top each cup. Place cups into a pan filled with enough cool water to come up an inch from the top of the cups.
Bake 35-40 minutes at 350°. Remove and cool.
Refrigerate until served.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Bias slice carrots about 1/2 inch thick.
Cook until tender (10 to 20 minutes).
Drain and combine sugar, cornstarch, ginger and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add orange juice and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Pour over hot carrots and toss to coat evenly.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Serves 6.

title: crusty beef, cheese and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Heat oil. Brown meat and onions. Add mushroom sauce, salt and pepper. Heat thoroughly.
Arrange in a casserole dish a layer of noodles, sauce and cheese. Repeat layers. Bake for 1 hour. Serves 8 to 10.

title: stewed onions
directions: Spray skillet with Pam or other spray.
Put all ingredients in pan.
Simmer on medium heat until onions are done.

title: fudge nut clusters
directions: Melt butter.
Add milk, peanuts and frosting mix.
Drop on wax paper and let set until firm.

title: egg and avocado dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Serve on crackers or as dip.

title: fish and cheese chowder
directions: Thaw frozen fish (enough to allow cutting).
Cut fish into 1-inch cubes.
Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add onion, carrot and celery.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Blend in flour, salt and paprika.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add chicken broth and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add fish.
Simmer until fish flakes easily (5 minutes for fresh, 10 minutes for frozen).
Add cheese; stir until melted. Serve hot.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut chuck in strips 1/2-inch thick.
Dredge with flour mixed with salt and brown in margarine in heavy skillet.
Add 2 cups water and remaining ingredients except last 3.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer 1/12 hours or until meat is tender.
Stir in mushrooms and sour cream and heat gently.
Serve with hot cooked noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato pecan pie
directions: Peel and cook sweet potato.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Saute pecans in butter until butter is golden brown.
Watch closely, will burn.
Add sweet potato and cool.
Combine eggs, corn syrup, sugar, vanilla, lemon juice and salt; mix thoroughly.
Add sweet potato-pecan mix.
Pour into shell.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 40 minutes or until set.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, microwave on High the butter and peanut butter (2 minutes). Stir until blended. Add remaining ingredients; stir until the lumps of sugar disappear. Microwave again on High ( 1 1/2 minutes); stir. Pour into buttered 9-inch square baking pan and plastic container. Store refrigerated. Cut into squares.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix and add 3 beaten egg yolks and milk.
Add this to dry ingredients.
Add 3/4 cup milk and cook over medium heat until thick.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into baked pie shells. Top with meringue.

title: sausage and egg strata
directions: Put buttered bread cubes into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix eggs, soup, milk and seasonings; pour over bread.
Add a layer of sausage.
Top with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° until egg mixture is set, approximately 45 minutes.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Moisten bread crumbs with water.
Put everything else, except oil, in bowl and mix loosely.
Shape into golf balls and fry a few at a time in the oil, until they are pretty brown.
Save drippings for Italian sauce.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Put roast in heavy skillet; brown on low to medium heat until well browned on both sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put in oven uncovered at 250° to 300°; cook about 2 to 3 hours or until done, keeping about 2 to 3 cups of water in it.
Slice in thin slices; place in casserole dish.
Mix barbecue sauce and some juice where meat was cooked.
Bring to a boil and pour over meat and heat.
It can sit overnight and be heated the next day.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix
with
hands;
roll out on floured board.
Cut with cutter.
Bake about 15 minutes at 400° in oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt and cornstarch.
Cook until clear. Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Cool thoroughly.
Spread strawberries into pie shells; pour cooled mixture over berries and chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Place in pie plate. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add rice and stir. Add broth and salt. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Cover and let set for 15 minutes.
Cook broccoli according to directions on package. Drain and add the Cheez Whiz, stirring to melt the cheese. Add chicken soup and rice to broccoli mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon chums
directions: Melt all ingredients except biscuits in a saucepan over medium-high heat.
Once melted, cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture in a cake pan; place biscuits on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in pan.
Mix together salad dressing and sugar.
Spread mixture on top of layered ingredients.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Let stand for 12 hours before serving.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat. Stir in crisp rice and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon on wax paper. Place in refrigerator until set.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add applesauce. Beat in eggs. Sift all dry ingredients. Coat nuts and fruit with 1 cup dry ingredients. Add to wet mixture.
Mix easily. Stir in rest of dry ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350°.

title: saucy chicken strips
