directions: Cut chicken breasts in 2 x 1/2-inch diagonal strips.
Melt butter in a large skillet; add chicken and brown on all sides. Remove chicken from skillet, reserving drippings.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms; saute until crisp-tender.
Return chicken to skillet.
In a small bowl, combine soup mix, water and Worcestershire sauce; mix well and pour over chicken.
Cover. Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove chicken to a warm platter.
Combine cornstarch and water; add to sauce.
Boil 1 minute or until thick.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Yields 4 servings.

title: war cake
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients for 5 minutes; let cool.
Add soda and flour to make a batter.
Add nuts or dried fruit to batter if desired.
Bake in slow oven (about 300°).

title: zucchini bread(yields 2 loaves)
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs. Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well. Add zucchini.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to mixture and lightly blend.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a cake tester inserted into center of loaf comes out clean.

title: eggs florentine
directions: Coat pan with little olive oil and cook on low heat in pan the eggs, goat cheese and dried tomato until light and fluffy. In a saute pan, add olive oil, garlic and spinach. Cook until spinach is just wilted. Toast muffins. Add spinach to muffin. Top with egg and Tarragon Sauce.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta per directions on package.
Rinse with cold water. Add green pepper, onions, olives and pepperoni.
Sprinkle with Italian dressing to taste.

title: crunchy casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Brown ground beef and drain. Combine all ingredients, except French fried onions.
Pour into 2 greased 2-quart casseroles.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and top with French fried onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: no cook karo candy
directions: Mix and knead with hands.
Tint or leave white.

title: cucumber souffle salad
directions: Prepare gelatin as directed on package, but use 1/2 cup less water.
Blend in rest of ingredients, except cucumbers, and place in freezer 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is firm around edges, but soft in center.
Place in a large bowl and whip until fluffy. Fold in cucumbers and chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish.

title: corn casserole
directions: In baking dish, melt oleo and cream cheese.
Add garlic salt. Mix until smooth.
Add drained corn.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Just before serving, add 7-Up. Makes about 40 cups.
Pour over crushed ice.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda.
In bowl cream sugar with shortening.
Add egg; beat well.
Add pineapple and vanilla. Stir in flour mixture.
Drop by rounded spoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salt water until tender; drain. Combine noodles, drained tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt. Blend soup and milk; heat through.
Add cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese is melted.
Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with almonds.
Bake in oven at 425° about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, water and sugar. Grind raw cranberries, apples, oranges and celery. Add fruit to Jell-O mixture.
Fold in nuts.

title: festive fruit trifle
directions: About 1 hour before serving or early in day, thaw frozen strawberries as label directs.
Meanwhile, drain peaches.
Cut pound cake lengthwise in half; cut each half crosswise into 1/2 inch thick slices.
In medium bowl prepare vanilla instant pudding and pie filling as label directs, but use only 1 1/2 cups milk and add almond extract.
With rubber spatula fold in 2 cups whipped topping until blended.
Reserve remaining whipped topping for garnish.
Drain syrup from 1 package thawed strawberries into 2 cup measure; add orange juice to syrup.
Drain remaining 2 packages strawberries but reserve their syrup for another day to use in juice or spoon over ice cream for dessert.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, chips and peanut butter.
Pour over cereal.
Put powdered sugar into trash bag.
Put cereal mixture in trash bag with powdered sugar and shake well.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix cool whip, lemonade, and milk until creamy.
Pour in pie crust and refrigerate overnight.

title: swiss steak casserole
directions: Mix flour with salt, pepper and paprika.
Rub steak with garlic and roll in seasoned flour.
Brown onions lightly in melted Spry.
Remove onions.
Sear meat quickly on both sides (not brown) and put in casserole, greased with Spry.
Place onions, rice and tomatoes on top of meat.
Add remainder of flour mixture to Spry in skillet and blend until smooth.
Add hot water gradually and cook until smooth.
Strain over meat in casserole.
Cook covered in moderate oven for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serves 6.

title: tojo's wacky wok chicken
directions: Pour oil into wok.
Heat on high.
Add chicken; season with a dash or two of red wine vinegar or soy sauce.
Stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes.
Add fresh vegetables.
Cover; cook for 3 to 5 minutes, or until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently.
Mix broth and cornstarch; pour over stir-fry.
Serve on bed of rice.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan, uncovered, on middle rack in 350° oven 45 minutes. (May be doubled.)

title: crazy crunch
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and corn syrup.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add nuts when thermometer reaches 245° and continue to cook and stir constantly until syrup reaches 290°.
Add vanilla and pour over popped corn in large bowl.
Mix with 2 large spoons until coated.
Spread on a baking sheet or wax paper.
Cool.
Break apart.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: lemon lush cake
directions: Make a pie crust by mixing ingredients thoroughly and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
It will be a golden brown.
Do not overbake.

title: my basic biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Cut in shortening until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Combine the egg, milk and honey; stir into flour mixture just until combined.
Turn onto a floured surface; knead 8 to 10 times.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a floured 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place 1-inch apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm. Yield:
10 biscuits.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: In a shallow dish, combine stuffing mix, Parmesan cheese, parsley and garlic powder; set aside.
Skin chicken; rinse and pat dry.
Brush chicken with margarine; coat with stuffing mixture. In greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch or 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, arrange pieces so they don't touch.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes or until tender and no longer pink.
Do not turn pieces while baking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean broccoli and separate into little pieces.
Put in a bowl.
Clean and cut green onions in small pieces.
Break bacon in small pieces.

title: potato biscuit
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add potatoes, stirring lightly.
Add milk and stir until a soft dough is formed.
Turn lightly 10 to 12 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on a lightly greased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: apple fudge nut pie
directions: *Toast walnuts in 300° oven 3 to 5 minutes.

title: mom's veggie dip
directions: Blend well.
This is too thick to be done in a blender! Make this the night before planning to use.
Great with cut vegetables, chips or crackers for parties.
Yields approximately 1 1/2 cups.

title: potato cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Put into a greased spring-form pan and brush the top with beaten egg.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Great with crisp, cold salad.

title: lazy oven stew
directions: Place layers of sliced potatoes in a 2-quart ovenware.
Layer onions and carrots over the potatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Place patties of hamburg on top of vegetable layers.
Mix the mushroom soup with the tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce; pour over layers. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Boil butter, milk, sugar and cocoa for 3 minutes.
Set off stove.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla to the boiled mixture.
Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper. Let cool.

title: bubbly cheese toast
directions: Cut each bread slice into 4 pieces.
Cut a cheese slice to fit each piece of bread; place on a cookie sheet. Broil until cheese is bubbly and lightly browned.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In
a
small saucepan, melt 1 cup margarine and 1/4 cup cocoa, then add water.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
In a large mixer bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, soda, cinnamon and	salt. Add
cocoa	mixture.
Beat	well.
Stir in 1/3 cup condensed milk,
eggs
and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10-inch
pan. Bake
minutes.	In
a
small saucepan, melt remaining
1/4 cup margarine; stir in remaining 1/4 cup cocoa and	remaining condensed
milk.
Add powdered sugar and nuts. Spread on warm cake.

title: easy make dill pickles
directions: Sterilize 6 quart jars; have lids ready.
Place 1 head dill, 1 slice onion, 1 clove garlic, pinch of crushed pepper and 1/4 teaspoon alum in each jar bottom, then pack with cucumbers, leaving space at top.
Bring to boil water, vinegar and salt. Pour over cucumbers in jar while still hot.
Seal.
Delicious.

title: ole fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add all other ingredients.
Make roll of dough.
Roll out; cut with cookie cutter or spoon out small balls.
Put on cookie sheet.

title: mildred's lime salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water thoroughly.
Add 1 (No. 2) can crushed pineapple.
Let it thicken, then add 1/2 cup chopped celery, 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 1 cup cottage cheese. Pour in 8-inch square dish and chill.
Serves 8.

title: corn and broccoli bake
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients; place in buttered 1-quart dish.
Mix cracker crumbs with remaining 2 tablespoons butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice krispies candy
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in a saucepan. Cook until sugar melts. Add peanut butter and melt. Add Rice Krispies. Stir well. Drop from a spoon onto wax paper. Let cool.

title: chicken and vegetable bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, mix soup, milk, vegetables and 1/2 can onions.
Cook chicken in frying pan with a small amount of oil until done.
Cool and dice.
Add to soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until hot.
Stir and sprinkle remaining onions on top.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: sausage balls
directions: Remove sausage from casings.
Mix thoroughly with other ingredients; roll into 1-inch balls.
Makes about 60 balls.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Can freeze on tray covered with plastic wrap until ready to reheat.

title: hamburger muffin meat cups
directions: Roll out each biscuit to 5-inch circle and put in greased muffin tin.
Brown hamburger.
Add mixture of catsup, brown sugar, vinegar and chili powder.
Fill muffin cups and bake at 375° for 18 minutes.
May flute the biscuits as for pie shell.

title: chicken sevilla
directions: Heat butter and oil in skillet.
Add chicken, skin side down, and cook for 10 minutes on medium-high.
Turn and cook 5 minutes. Add green pepper, tomato, oranges (separated into segments and cut in half).
Add to chicken; cover and cook over low heat for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple cottage cheese salad
directions: Round cottage cheese on top of pineapple ring.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Yield:
1 serving.
Carbohydrate 7 g, protein 8 g, fat 2 g, calories 78.
One serving = 1 meat low-fat exchange, 1/2 fruit exchange.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, kneading to mix well. Spread in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Yields 64 (1-inch) squares, about 80 calories each.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Preheat a 10-inch skillet, uncovered, over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Melt butter and add steak slices and onion.
Brown about 5 minutes.
Add bouillon cube and water.
Cover; reduce heat to low and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add soup, salt and pepper, stirring to blend.
Cover and heat 10 minutes.
Add sour cream, stirring to blend.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Serve over hot cooked egg noodles.

title: wassail
directions: Simmer for 2 hours.
Add:
1 sliced orange, 1 sliced lemon. Serve hot.

title: pineapple sausage
directions: In
Dutch
oven,
steam sausage and remove until later. In the same liquid, steam celery, onions and bell pepper.	Now cut up sausage in bite-size pieces.
When vegetables are done, add sausage and tomatoes.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Drain pineapple juice
and	reserve it.
Cut pineapple in 1/2-inch pieces while still
in
the
can and add.
Cook for 15 minutes.	Add cornstarch to pineapple juice to thicken gravy and cook for 15 minutes.

title: red chicken stew
directions: Saute onions in a small amount of oil and set aside.
In a heavy saucepan, put the tomato soup, chicken and water as needed. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add onions.
Cook on low to medium heat until chicken is ready to "fall away" from the bones.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice in 1 teaspoon salt and 3 cups water.
When nearly done, brown hamburger, drain fat and add carrots, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir-fry until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Roll crackers; add eggs, tuna, 1/2 can soup, salt and pepper. Make into loaf.
Put rest of soup on top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef into 1 x 1/2-inch strips.
Brown in 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir bouillon, catsup, garlic and salt into the skillet; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms and onion.
Cover and simmer another 5 minutes. Gradually stir in flour.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Reduce heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through. Serve over hot noodles.

title: old world sauerkraut supper
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces; fry and drain.
Add flour to drippings and blend.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Mix well.
Place in crock-pot.
Add other ingredients and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours (high, 3 to 4 hours).

title: glazed ham
directions: Put jelly, onion, lemon and mustard in blender, cover and run on blend until smooth.
Place ham or slices in baking dish or pan and cover with sauce from blender.
Bake in 325° oven until ham is tender.

title: mrs. lyndon b. johnson's recipe for pedernales river chili
directions: Sear meat, onion and garlic in large, heavy boiler or skillet until light brown.
Add seasonings, tomatoes and hot water.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer about 1 hour.
As chili cooks, skim off fat.

title: saccharin pickles
directions: Bring the vinegar, water and saccharin to a rolling boil.
Drop in medium cucumbers a few at a time.
Stir around in solution until color begins to change; don't leave in vinegar solution too long or they may get soft.
Pack in jars.
Add 2 teaspoons of salt per quart.
Cover well with vinegar solution.
Seal.

title: grandma's fudge
directions: In large pan bring sugar and milk to a boil.
Boil gently for 10 minutes.
In large bowl combine chocolate chips, marshmallows, butter and vanilla.
Pour in sugar syrup and blend well with beaters.
Pour into buttered platter.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours. Add nuts, if desired.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Melt butter in skillet; saute onion until transparent.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt, curry powder and pepper.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add water to make 1/2 cup liquid. Gradually stir into flour mixture in skillet.
Blend in milk until smooth.
Add mushrooms.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick.
Arrange broccoli and chicken on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sauce over.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Cool for 15 minutes before serving.

title: coronation chicken
directions: Skin chicken.
Cook, remove bones and cube.
Cool.
Peel and finely chop onions; cooking oil until soft.
Add mango chutney, stock, tomato puree, curry powder and lemon juice.
Mix well and simmer, uncovered, for about 10 minutes until mixture reduces. Cool.
Mix mayonnaise and cream together.
When other sauce has cooled, mix together.
(More cream can be added if wished.)
Roast almonds under grill until brown and mix in 3/4 of them (when cool) into sauce together with cooled chicken.
Sprinkle almonds over the top.

title: italian mushroom salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Marinate at least three hours in refrigerator, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour melted butter in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crushed graham cracker crumbs on top of butter.
Add chopped nuts over crumbs, chocolate chip pieces and coconut.
Pour condensed milk over all the above ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly brown on top.
Allow 15 minutes to cool. Cut into small bars.

title: clam sauce
directions: Fry garlic, onion and pimento lightly in skillet.
Add tomatoes, sherry and clam juice.
Cook until reduced and thickened.
Add clams.
Simmer 2 to 5 minutes.
Add parsley last minute.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
When cool, add beaten eggs, dry ingredients, milk, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: luscious chocolate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, graham cracker crumbs and sugar; press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 5 minutes, or until set.
Cool, then refrigerate.

title: peach nutty cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour peaches with juice into pan evenly.
Sprinkle peaches with cake mix.
Drizzle butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: clam chowder
directions: Strain liquid from clams, reserving 1/2 cup.
In large pot, saut onions, then add reserved clam liquid, potatoes and water. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer until potatoes are tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Stir in clams.
Blend 1/4 cup milk into flour, then blend into remaining milk.
Stir into chowder with half and half and cook, stirring until boiling.
Add salt and pepper; stir and serve with soup crackers with a dab of butter.
Can add a dash of Tabasco sauce.

title: crab casserole
directions: Saute green peppers and onion in margarine.
Combine with other ingredients.
Put in baking dish and bake 20 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: twinkie treat
directions: Cut Twinkies in half; line medium deep cake pan.
Top with Cool Whip.
Put a layer of the cut strawberries on the Cool Whip. Drizzle with the strawberry glaze.
Put another layer of Twinkies, topped with Cool Whip, more cut strawberries and another drizzle of strawberry glaze.

title: barbecue chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken in oleo or Crisco.
Saute onion, celery and pepper in oleo.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.
Bake in covered casserole dish.

title: hawaiian pork
directions: Brown meat in margarine.
Cover tightly and simmer until meat is tender.
Add vinegar, pineapple juice, celery and bell pepper. Simmer until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, stir constantly until mixture thickens.
Serves 50 family style or 60 to 65 plates.

title: bucket bread
directions: Cover raisins and margarine with boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.

title: squash pudding
directions: Cut
squash
in
slices.
Cook	in
water until tender. Drain and
mash
with potato masher.
Stir in 3 rounded tablespoonfuls flour
and	1/2 stick margarine.
Add sugar and eggs and beat well, then add evaporated milk, vanilla and coconut. Mix well. Place in greased 8 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch casserole.
May sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg, if desired.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, vinegar, spices and onion.
Boil for a few minutes and then add cucumber slices.
Continue to boil until cucumbers change color.
Fill jars and seal.

title: pineapple-butter dish
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add condensed milk.
Add large can drained pineapple and 6 slices of bread (cubed).
Mix in 3 eggs (beaten).
Grease pan and bake approximately 40 minutes at 350°.

title: *pita venita(raised dough pita with onions)
directions: Mix the above thoroughly and knead well.
Place dough in bowl and cover. Allow to rise for 1 hour.
After dough has risen, divide dough into 2 balls.
Oil baking pan (14 x 17-inch) with olive oil.

title: texas black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Brown ground chuck, garlic and onion.
Add the remaining ingredients, except the chips and cheeses.
Place a layer of tortilla chips in the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Spoon the meat mixture over the chips until just covered.
Cover the meat mixture with more tortilla chips. Cover the chips with one cup of cheese.
Spoon the remaining meat mixture over the cheese and top with more tortilla chips and the remaining cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven when mixture is bubbling and cheese has melted.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: mary buford's pork chops
directions: Flour and brown pork chops, quickly.
Lay pork chops in casserole.
Place
following
on
top:
Slice tomatoes, onion, carrots.
Then
slice
potatoes to fill casserole.
Add 1-inch water, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and serve.
Pork chops so tender, cut with a fork.

title: hodge podge soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion, salt and pepper to taste and drain. Add remaining ingredients.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Then add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna on a bun
directions: Split and toast sandwich buns.
Spread lower halves of buns with tuna salad made by combining tuna fish, celery, onion and mayonnaise to moisten.
Over salad sprinkle grated cheese and top with a tablespoon of chili sauce.
Slide buns back under broiler to melt cheese.
Buns and cheese are hot.
Salad stays crisp and cool. Makes 6 sandwiches.
Can be made with chicken instead of tuna.

title: ham and potato bake
directions: Dilute soup with milk.
Alternate potatoes, ham, onion and soup mixture in baking dish.
Make sure potatoes and ham are covered to prevent drying.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour covered; uncover and bake until potatoes are done.

title: stuffed crabmeat potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes, either in oven or microwave.
Cut in half and scoop out insides.
Be careful not to tear skins.
Mash potato, butter, sour cream and seasonings (except paprika) until smooth. Stir in crabmeat.
Lay potato skins on a cookie sheet and fill. Sprinkle with paprika and grated cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat together eggs, granulated sugar and salad oil.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder.
Gradually add to egg, oil and sugar mixture.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan that is greased and floured.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: If you like hot pickles, add a few hot peppers.
Wash cucumbers and slice thin.
Chop onions and pepper.
Combine salt and cucumbers; let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in large kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Add drained cucumbers. Heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Pack while hot into hot, sterilized jars and seal at once.
These are delicious with vegetables and fish.

title: fresh fig cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs until mixed.
Measure out 2 cups fresh figs.
Mash well and mix into mixture.
Mix well.
Mix well with other mixture the flour, cinnamon, allspice and salt.
Then flour and grease Bundt pan.
Pour mixture in and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken breasts; skin and bone them, then thick slice or chunk them.
Arrange broccoli in large baking dish, then place chicken on top.
Mix soups, mayonnaise and lemon juice together. Spread mixture over the broccoli and chicken.
(It will be rather thick; try to work the mixture down through the chicken and broccoli.)
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in refrigerator and let set until morning.
Cook in oven 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: candy bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first eight ingredients together. Shape 1 tablespoon dough around each Snicker bar.
Roll to form a ball.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack. Drizzle with melted chocolate.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all together and let congeal.

title: cajun fried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and place in a large Tupperware container. Cover with buttermilk.
Add hot sauce.
Stir to blend with chicken.
Marinate in refrigerator for 6-8 hours.
Just before frying, combine flour with salt, pepper, and Cajun seasoning in a large plastic bag.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease cookie sheets. In a large bowl, beat 1 1/4 cups sugar, shortening and vanilla until fluffy. Beat in eggs, then bananas. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Beat into sugar mixture. Stir in walnuts. Chill 30 minutes. Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart on cookie sheets. Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over cookies.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 5 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°. Makes one casserole.

title: squash delight
directions: Cook squash with salt and pepper to taste until just tender. Drain and mash.
Mix sour cream and soup; add onion and carrot. Fold into mashed squash.
Place mixture in greased baking dish. Prepare cornbread dressing and spread over squash mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook salt pork; fry onions in salt pork.
Cut up potatoes and cook in water until almost done.
Add can of clams and quart of milk.
Heat slowly.
Do not boil.
Serves 4.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips over low heat. Pour over cereal.
Mix well until coated.
Put in brown bag, add powdered sugar; shake until well coated.
Enjoy!

title: jello mold
directions: Put Jell-O in mixing bowl.
Add boiling water and strawberries.
Put into refrigerator until starting to thicken. Then add Cool Whip.
Pour into mold.

title: classic lasagne
directions: Brown meat; add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, salt, parsley, garlic, Italian seasoning, pepper and oregano.
Simmer uncovered about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles while preparing sauce.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spread 1 cup sauce.
Then alternate layers of noodles, sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese, ending with sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Allow to stand for 5 minutes.

title: tim's surprise cake
directions: Stir cake mix and pie filling together (very thick).
Combine eggs, vanilla, oil and nuts; add to cake mix and blend well. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and serve plain or frost with vanilla icing with 1 teaspoon cherry extract mixed in.

title: sissy's chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add water, add onion and add green pepper. Add chili powder.
Add garlic powder.
Add tomato paste.
The longer it cooks the better chili is.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, soy sauce, sugar and ginger.
Add chicken, celery, water chestnuts, pepper and onions; mix lightly.
Chill several hours.
Serve on spinach covered platter; sprinkle with noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tacos
directions: Brown ground beef in large frypan; drain.
Add next three ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Heat shells in 250° oven for 3 minutes.
Set remaining ingredients out buffet style for everyone to assemble their own taco!

title: chinese spareribs
directions: Combine ingredients into marinade; marinate about 2 hours, turning often.
Broil 45 to 50 minutes, turning and basting often. Serves 4 to 5.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Combine all ingredients except 1 cup nuts.
Use this cup of nuts to roll ball in.
Serve with Ritz crackers.
This can be frozen.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add juice from pineapple and beverage.
Chill until medium-stiff. Whip with mixer until foamy.
Gradually whip into whipped topping. Fold in pineapple.
Pour into mold and chill until set.
Makes approximately 8 servings.
Calories: 58.

title: chocolate chip walnut pie
directions: Mix each ingredient in order.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Combine the chocolate and heavy cream.
Stir constantly over low heat until the chocolate melts.
Remove the chocolate mixture from the heat; stir in the butter.
The sauce is now ready to be used.

title: caramel, pecan, coconut pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; add coconut and chopped pecans. Cook until brown; put aside.
Combine cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk and beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping. Layer 1/4 of cream cheese mixture into each pie.
Sprinkle 1/4 of coconut mixture evenly over each pie.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Let frozen pie stand at room temperature before slicing.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook beef, bacon & onions in a large skillet until meat loses color and onions are tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in catsup, salt, mustard & vinegar.
Combine remaining ingedients in 3 qt. casserole dish.
Stir in meat mixture & cover.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix in bowl and beat 2 minutes the flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla, pudding, margarine, egg and milk.
Grease and flour the bottom and sides of 10-inch pie pan.
Place batter in pan. Arrange peaches over batter.
Combine softened cream cheese with 3 tablespoons of reserved juice and beat 2 minutes.
Spoon within 1-inch of edge of batter.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over cream cheese.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to wet mixture.
Mix lightly.
Turn into greased muffin tin and bake in preheated oven at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: meatballs in spicy sauce
directions: Mix and form meatballs.
Place in 9 x 11 pan.

title: reunion chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in large sauce pan.
Cook onions in butter until soft.
Stir in soups and water.
Spread rice in ungreased casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over rice.
Pour about half the soup mixture into casserole and stir well.
Arrange chicken in casserole.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken. Bake, uncovered at 275° for 3 hours.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Add all ingredients except stuffing. Place in large casserole dish. Top with stuffing. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: appetizer crab quiches
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine crab meat, carrot, cheese, onion, flour, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Spoon 1/4 of mixture into each scallop shell.
Arrange shells on serving platter.
Set aside.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; let stand until partially congealed.
Then take egg beater and whip jello.
Then whip cream; add 1 Tbsp. sugar to cream and fold into jello.
Add pineapple. Put in refrigerator;
Stir several times before serving.

title: party wieners
directions: In skillet (electric works best), put small amount of oil or shortening.
Chop all wieners into fourths.
Put in hot skillet. Brown quickly.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes; add sugar gradually.
Add remaining ingredients.
Combine all ingredients.
Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Remove; invert while hot.
Take a towel and dust with powdered sugar.
Roll up and let cool.

title: antipasto salad(six main course servings or 12 first course servings)
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, olives, pepperoni, green pepper, garbanzo beans, mushrooms and artichoke hearts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and graham cracker crumbs.
Pack in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, vanilla, eggs and 2 sticks margarine at high speed for 15 minutes, no less.
Spread over crumbs.
Put bananas on top of whipped mixture, then add drained pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over this.
Sprinkle on nuts and add cherries.
Set in refrigerator until cooled.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 6 tablespoons of juice. Pour pineapple in a casserole dish.
Mix flour, sugar and 6 tablespoons of juice in a bowl until smooth.
Pour mixture over pineapple. Add cheese. Sprinkle crackers on top.
Melt margarine and pour over the top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: simple cabbage slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight. Yield: 6 servings.

title: barbecued water chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon slices into 3 pieces.
Wrap bacon piece around each water chestnut; secure with toothpick.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix sugars with catsup in bowl.
Dip each wrapped water chestnut in sauce; arrange in baking dish. Pour remaining sauce over top.
Bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, top with bread crumbs.
Cover and bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove cover and bake another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coodies
directions: Soak codfish overnight.
The next morning, drain off water. Place codfish in saucepan; cover with fresh water and bring to boiling.
Boil until tender (about 45 minutes to an hour).
Drain and cool.
If not boneless, debone codfish, flaking with a fork as you go along.
Add cooked, mashed potatoes, butter, onion, parsley, baking powder and eggs.
Salt and pepper, if desired. Combine and mash mixture with a large fork or beat with electric mixer.
Shape into cakes or balls.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown all around.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Place the boned chicken breasts in a pan.
Thoroughly drain sauerkraut; put on each piece of chicken.
Place a slice of Swiss cheese on each; pour dressing over each.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: glorified rice(salad or dessert)
directions: Drain all canned fruits well, reserving 1 1/2 cups juice.
(If you use all the juice from the cherries, it will make your rice a pretty pink!)
Cook rice in this liquid per package directions (except no salt or butter).
Cool rice completely.
In large bowl, toss rice with fruits and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Serve thoroughly chilled.

title: chip beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in baking dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Melt the butter or margarine in a small bowl.
Beat the eggs with vanilla.
In a large bowl combine the sugars, syrup and melted butter.
Add the egg mixture and mix well.
Put pecans in the pie shell and pour in the sugar egg mixture.
Bake at 450°for 10 minutes.
Reduce the heat to 350° and bake 35 to 45 minutes until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: hot cucumber relish
directions: Heat oil in medium-size skillet over medium heat.
Add red pepper and white parts of green onion; saute 2 minutes.
Add the cucumber; saute 3 minutes or until cucumber is tender-crisp. Remove from heat.
Stir in green parts of onion, lime juice, honey, mint and salt.
Serve hot or warm.
Can be served with fish, meat or poultry.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and seasonings. Drain well. Dump in shell. Spread chilies on top. Drain mushrooms and spread on top of chilies. Shred cheese. Pour egg mixture onto pie. Try to pour some mixture between shell and pie plate. Bake in a 400° oven until shell browns. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake until cheese melts. Serves 4 to 6.

title: jam cake and filling
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Stir soda into buttermilk.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add jam last.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8 inch pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons of cocoa, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Add milk and shortening; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased 9-inch square cake pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour 1 3/4 cups of hot tap water over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares while hot.
Spoon sauce over each serving.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix butter, flour and chopped nuts together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: b.b.'s crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
If you like hot, add more Texas Pete or Tabasco.
Form into patties and fry in small amount of oil.
These may be frozen.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and oil.
Add sugar and beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well again.
Combine flour and soda and add to mixture with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together with mixer at medium speed.
Pour into greased pie pan or 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: butterscotch krispies
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch in a saucepan.
Mix Rice Krispies in until they are all coated.
Put in 9-inch buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: red snapper on grill
directions: Marinate fish. Spray grill with Pam. Grill 10 minutes or until meat is flaky.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple (juice and all) with the pudding mix.
Add the whipped cream and marshmallows.
Let stand a few hours.
It makes a quick salad.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in chunks.
Boil in salt water until tender; drain.
Add slightly beaten egg, onion, cheese, milk and seasonings.
Mix well and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks and milk together.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together, then melted butter.
Fold in egg whites.
Have griddle hot.
Drop in pan, turning once.
Serve with syrup.
